Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.46,0:00:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We extend a warm welcome to one and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.96,0:00:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In this session, which corresponds
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.26,0:00:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Saturday afternoon portion\Nof the program,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.68,0:00:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we will learn what we individually can do
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.76,0:00:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to pursue peace with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.68,0:00:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We will begin\Nwith a music-video presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.02,0:00:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The video will encourage us\Nto welcome others
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.48,0:00:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,into our peaceful worldwide brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.69,0:00:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Please enjoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.64,0:10:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Please join in singing\Nsong number 29, entitled
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.85,0:10:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“Living Up to Our Name”—song number 29.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.67,0:12:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, our imperfections\Ncan disrupt our peace
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.22,0:12:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and that of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.51,0:13:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,During the next symposium,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.52,0:13:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we will consider things we must avoid
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.60,0:13:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to cultivate peaceful relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.77,0:13:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Please give your attention\Nto Brother Harold Corkern,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.36,0:13:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a helper to the Publishing Committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.90,0:13:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as he develops the theme
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.24,0:13:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Put Away’ Peace Wreckers\N—Inappropriate Boasting.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.09,0:13:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What comes to your mind\Nwhen you hear the expression “put away”?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.92,0:13:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You may think of related expressions
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.01,0:13:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,such as “cast aside,” “dispose of,”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.68,0:13:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“discard,” “get rid of.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.19,0:13:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What did we have to put away\Nto become a Christian?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.48,0:13:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible in the book
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.48,0:13:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of Ephesians 4:22\Nprovides the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.28,0:13:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Ephesians 4:22:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.07,0:14:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“You were taught\Nto put away the old personality
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.83,0:14:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“that conforms\Nto your former course of conduct
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.92,0:14:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is being corrupted\Naccording to its deceptive desires.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.67,0:14:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So we had “to put away the old personality.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.97,0:14:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s one thing to put it away;
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.30,0:14:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s something else to keep it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.26,0:14:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s why\Nin the very next verse, verse 23,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.43,0:14:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul encourages us to do this:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.02,0:14:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“And you should continue to be made new
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.56,0:14:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in your dominant mental attitude.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.53,0:14:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s so important to keep it away,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.07,0:14:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because the old personality has traits
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.86,0:14:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that can become peace wreckers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.41,0:14:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This symposium\Nwill consider five peace wreckers
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.17,0:14:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that we should put away and keep away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.00,0:14:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Each talk will include\Nthe following main points:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.01,0:14:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,(1) It will define the peace wrecker,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.76,0:15:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,(2) it will explain how it wrecks peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.51,0:15:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and (3) we will consider how to put it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.98,0:15:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the very first one\Nthat we’re going to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.90,0:15:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It is inappropriate boasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.24,0:15:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What is inappropriate boasting?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.86,0:15:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, it’s self-praise,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.62,0:15:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Bible condemns self-praise
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.41,0:15:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice Proverbs 27:2:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.96,0:15:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let someone else praise you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.33,0:15:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“and not your own mouth;
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.50,0:15:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,others, and not your own lips.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.30,0:15:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-praise is an evidence of pride
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.80,0:15:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that causes one\Nto elevate himself above others.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.35,0:15:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Some might develop an unhealthy pride
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.18,0:15:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,about their accomplishments,\Neven in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.44,0:15:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened in the first century.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.77,0:15:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul had to write\Nto the Corinthian congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.61,0:15:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,about the dissensions that they were having,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.78,0:16:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the lack of peace they were experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.87,0:16:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.20,0:16:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, some in the congregation\Nwere “puffed up with pride” about themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.33,0:16:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,or other men,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.33,0:16:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,such as Paul, Apollos, Cephas.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.00,0:16:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They were giving\Ntoo much attention to themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.80,0:16:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and to other men.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.80,0:16:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how could that happen today?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.55,0:16:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s imagine\Na group of brothers talking,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.76,0:16:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and one in the group says,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.06,0:16:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“With Jehovah’s help\Nand with diligent prayer and effort,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.56,0:16:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I finally got a Bible study.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.81,0:16:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But right away,\Nanother one in the group proudly declares,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.86,0:16:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have four Bible studies;
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.11,0:16:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,two are attending meetings,\Nand one will soon be baptized.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.12,0:16:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Could such a statement be a peace wrecker?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.45,0:16:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How does inappropriate boasting\Nwreck peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.46,0:16:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s not wrong\Nto take pleasure in our work
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.59,0:17:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and to thank Jehovah\Nfor the success that we may have.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.59,0:17:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But inappropriate boasting\Nabout our accomplishments
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.72,0:17:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,can stir up competition, envy, and rivalry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.98,0:17:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We must remember that self-promotion
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.60,0:17:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,does not originate\Nwith our heavenly Father, “the God of peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.77,0:17:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does it originate?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.07,0:17:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,First John 2:16 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.36,0:17:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“The showy display of one’s means of life
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.20,0:17:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“does not originate with the Father,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.49,0:17:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but originates with the world.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.49,0:17:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And would you not agree\Nthat the world is filled with self-praise?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.50,0:17:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Even on their social media, we see this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.75,0:17:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the material\Nthat people post on social media
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.80,0:17:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is designed to make one\Nappear very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.80,0:17:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is a showy display
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.80,0:17:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of their accomplishments,\Ntheir material possessions,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.64,0:17:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or their expensive vacations that they enjoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.98,0:17:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, it’s all about “look at me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.61,0:18:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we want to avoid getting caught up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.15,0:18:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world’s spirit of self-promotion
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.95,0:18:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that wrecks peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.57,0:18:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To illustrate just how devastating
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.04,0:18:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the peace wrecker’s\Ninappropriate boasting can be,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.83,0:18:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s briefly consider\Nthe Bible character Haman.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.83,0:18:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a proud and haughty man,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.30,0:18:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and he boasted a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.34,0:18:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Esther chapter 5 tells us
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.38,0:18:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was boasting\Nwith his family and friends
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.72,0:18:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,about his wealth, his many sons,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.55,0:18:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,how the king had promoted him\Nto a high station,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.43,0:18:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was above all the other servants,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.64,0:18:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he’d had a special meal, or banquet,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.48,0:18:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,with the king and queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.86,0:18:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But Haman was hateful and arrogant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.69,0:18:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was plotting to kill\NJehovah’s faithful servant Mordecai.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.87,0:18:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But his scheme\Nand his attitudes were exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.08,0:18:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.95,0:18:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The very stake that Haman had built
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.04,0:18:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to hang Mordecai on he was hung on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.17,0:19:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And it reminds us\N—doesn’t it?—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.38,0:19:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that at Isaiah 29:20, the Bible says:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.38,0:19:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“The boaster will come to his finish.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.72,0:19:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So because of the devastating effects
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.81,0:19:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that improper boasting\Ncan have on ourselves and others,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.14,0:19:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we do not even want\Nto give the impression of boasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.61,0:19:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.94,0:19:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how a sister’s actions
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.28,0:19:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,are misunderstood as boasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.91,0:19:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“Put away from yourselves every kind
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.29,0:19:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“of malicious bitterness, anger, wrath,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.67,0:19:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“screaming, and abusive speech,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.59,0:19:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as everything injurious.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.97,0:19:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Did anyone start the day thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.30,0:19:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I believe I’ll show malicious bitterness\Nto my brother today’?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.18,0:19:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.27,0:19:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet the potential is there, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.77,0:20:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But genuine affection fights peace wreckers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.90,0:20:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And affection grows when we really know\Nour brothers and sisters well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.90,0:20:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We remember their joys
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.03,0:20:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and pains,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.58,0:20:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,their selfless zeal,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.41,0:20:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,how they came to love Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.04,0:20:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and what they endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.51,0:20:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll get back as soon as I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.01,0:20:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Love you. Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.43,0:20:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.18,0:20:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Haley, love?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.52,0:20:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So sorry, I’ve got to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.02,0:20:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. I’ll ring you about this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.86,0:20:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks. Love you both.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.44,0:20:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.94,0:20:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The afternoon would look better.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.28,0:20:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nana!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.24,0:20:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Haley, darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.16,0:20:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so, so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.12,0:20:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it’s not too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.91,0:20:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.66,0:20:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.67,0:21:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you though?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.71,0:21:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. I’m so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.38,0:21:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, poor thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.42,0:21:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me clear this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.85,0:21:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.81,0:21:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Nana, it’s Sunday today, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.81,0:21:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.15,0:21:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s felt like such a long day, hasn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.86,0:21:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It has felt like a long day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.07,0:21:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.95,0:21:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sleep well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.65,0:22:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.78,0:22:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Haley from DeNure Design here,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.12,0:22:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,helping you to be effortlessly elegant.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.54,0:22:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to welcome my new followers\Nand thank everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.12,0:22:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,for subscribing to this channel.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.33,0:22:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So first up, I’ve got\Nthis gorgeous earring and necklace set.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.34,0:22:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you can see, the first disc I’ve done\Nis in this warm nude tone,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.05,0:22:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s great because it goes . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.55,0:22:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you believe her?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.68,0:22:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Haley’s business feed?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.43,0:22:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But what makes this set is really special.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.43,0:22:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s giving you\Nthat understated elegant look.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.35,0:22:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If you haven’t done so already,\Nplease hit the subscribe button below.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.73,0:22:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because as you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.48,0:22:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,when you look this good, you feel great.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.29,0:23:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Was the sister in this video\Nboasting inappropriately?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.75,0:23:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she was a humble servant of Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.25,0:23:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,kindly and patiently\Nhelping her elderly relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.67,0:23:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But do you recall her business website
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.80,0:23:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the presentation she made\Nabout her jewelry products?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.35,0:23:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She said,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.39,0:23:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“When you look this good,\Nyou feel great.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.31,0:23:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Her Christian sister was upset
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.15,0:23:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and took those comments and her actions
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.49,0:23:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to be boastful.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.70,0:23:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this video reminds us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.70,0:23:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to think about how our words and our actions
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.83,0:23:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,may appear to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.41,0:23:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we’re going to get to the question:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.96,0:23:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we put away inappropriate boasting?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.34,0:23:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A key point that we must always remember
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.63,0:23:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to help us to do just that\Nis recorded in the book
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.51,0:23:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of 1 Corinthians 4:7,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.97,0:24:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Corinthians 4:7:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.52,0:24:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“For who makes you different from another?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.39,0:24:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“Indeed, what do you have\Nthat you did not receive?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.23,0:24:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“If, in fact, you did receive it,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.78,0:24:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,why do you boast\Nas though you did not receive it?”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.99,0:24:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the point of this scripture?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.37,0:24:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We do not want to boast about ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.12,0:24:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but give all credit to Jehovah\Nfor the good that we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.08,0:24:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, some people are proud\Nabout their good looks,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.17,0:24:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,their popularity,\Ntheir wealth, their position,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.46,0:24:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,their physical strength,\Ntheir musical ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.05,0:24:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But remember, King David of ancient Israel
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.06,0:24:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,had all of those assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.22,0:24:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But throughout his entire life,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.43,0:24:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,he never became a boastful person.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.81,0:24:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He remained humble.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.81,0:24:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.61,0:24:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,At Psalm 113:5-8,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.57,0:24:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,David gave all credit to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.11,0:25:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that in his case\NJehovah stooped down
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.62,0:25:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and took this “lowly” one\Nand raised him up
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.00,0:25:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to “sit with nobles.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.67,0:25:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And on every occasion that he had,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.17,0:25:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,David would always say, ‘Praise Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.21,0:25:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,boast about his holy name.’
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.38,0:25:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we, like David,\Nshould “boast in Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.10,0:25:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul encouraged us to do that\Nat 1 Corinthians 1:31:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.43,0:25:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“The one who boasts,\Nlet him boast in Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.60,0:25:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.86,0:25:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that we boast in the privilege\Nof knowing the true God
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.19,0:25:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and of being able\Nto be used by him to accomplish his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.08,0:25:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, another way\Nthat we can put away improper boasting
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.00,0:25:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is to not talk about ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.75,0:25:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but to acknowledge the good\Nand the fine qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.17,0:25:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that our fellow workers have.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.34,0:26:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Humble and modest people\Ndon’t brag about what they do,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.05,0:26:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but they turn their attention\Nto their fellow workers
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.64,0:26:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and see how Jehovah is using them
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.81,0:26:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and blessing them in his service.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.35,0:26:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.35,0:26:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that creates a very peaceful,\Nhappy environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.48,0:26:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, may we continue\Nto put away and keep away
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.03,0:26:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,inappropriate boasting—self-praise.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.91,0:26:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.41,0:26:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,By giving praise and thanks and honor\Nto Jehovah for our accomplishments
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.08,0:26:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and by commending our fellow workers\Nfor all the good qualities they have
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.92,0:26:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and for how Jehovah\Nis using them in his service.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.25,0:26:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,By doing so, we will preserve\Nour precious possession of peace
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.88,0:26:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,with Jehovah and with our brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.89,0:26:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Seth Hyatt,\Na helper to the Service Committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.27,0:26:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,will now present\Nthe next talk of this symposium,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.27,0:26:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Put Away’ Peace Wreckers—Envy.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.66,0:27:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What is envy?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.66,0:27:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.33,0:27:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s important that we be able to identify\Nthe symptoms of envy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.83,0:27:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.83,0:27:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because envy is an expression\Nof hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.96,0:27:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s an enemy of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.46,0:27:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And if left unchecked,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.76,0:27:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it can result in spiritual death.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.72,0:27:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,As described in the Bible,\Nenvy has two symptoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.73,0:27:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is probably more familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.65,0:27:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,An envious person wants
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.06,0:27:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,what someone else has.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.15,0:27:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the second symptom
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.15,0:27:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that makes envy especially dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.16,0:27:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,An envious person not only wants\Nwhat someone else has,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.16,0:27:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but he also doesn’t want\Nthe other person to have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.29,0:27:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s an example:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.50,0:28:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In the first century,\NJewish religious leaders envied Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.34,0:28:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because Jesus was much appreciated\Nby the common people.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.35,0:28:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus dealt with people,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.43,0:28:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,including lowly ones,\Nin a way that dignified them.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.35,0:28:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, he was appreciated.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.36,0:28:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The religious leaders envied him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.11,0:28:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But rather than adjusting their own way\Nof dealing with people,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.03,0:28:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,they attacked Jesus verbally
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.37,0:28:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in an effort to destroy\Nhis good reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.16,0:28:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They spread malicious slander.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.71,0:28:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only did they want\Nwhat Jesus had,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.42,0:28:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but also they didn’t want\NJesus to have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.55,0:28:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder envy is listed\Nas one of “the works of the flesh”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.84,0:28:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,at Galatians 5:21.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.06,0:28:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a dangerous quality
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.73,0:28:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that we need to avoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.94,0:29:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How does envy disrupt peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.90,0:29:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Envy undermines, damages,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.82,0:29:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,or even destroys relationships
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.54,0:29:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in the family and in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.75,0:29:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider the example of Jacob
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.58,0:29:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and his 12 sons.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.50,0:29:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jacob had special affection\Nfor one of his sons, Joseph.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.59,0:29:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result,\NJoseph’s brothers became envious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.76,0:29:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How did the envy manifest itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.60,0:29:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the fruitage?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.44,0:29:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they dealt treacherously\Nwith Joseph, selling him into slavery.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.48,0:29:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And as if that weren’t bad enough,\Nthey compounded their wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.11,0:29:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,by lying to Jacob,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.74,0:29:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,telling him that Joseph was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.16,0:29:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the Bible account,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.37,0:29:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Jacob “refused to be comforted.”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.71,0:30:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He mourned Joseph for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.17,0:30:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What a terrible consequence of envy!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.01,0:30:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s clear that envy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.59,0:30:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,allows no room for love,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.26,0:30:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,compassion, or kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.72,0:30:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Those qualities go out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.98,0:30:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And they’re replaced by qualities
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.02,0:30:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,such as hatred, strife, fits of anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.86,0:30:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Can envy disrupt the peace\Nof a congregation?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.49,0:30:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider the examples\Nof Korah, Dathan, and Abiram.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.70,0:30:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They envied Moses and Aaron
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.46,0:30:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in the congregation of Israel.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.42,0:30:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How did that envy manifest itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.09,0:30:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they began\Nto speak negatively—critically—
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.26,0:30:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s representatives,\Neven accusing Moses
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.68,0:30:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of playing the prince\Nand lifting himself up above the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.60,0:31:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They forgot that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.40,0:31:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,had put Moses and Aaron\Nin their positions of responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.28,0:31:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Jehovah react
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.20,0:31:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to that manifestation of envy?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.62,0:31:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He destroyed those three men\Nand all who supported them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.87,0:31:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,For a time, the congregation\Nwas robbed of its peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.71,0:31:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and the accounts\Ncertainly provide some insight
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.96,0:31:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,into Jehovah’s view of envy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.51,0:31:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, by this point,\Nyou’re no doubt thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.51,0:31:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I would never want something\Nso badly that I would
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.22,0:31:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,damage someone else to get it.’
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.85,0:31:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But we’re all imperfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.85,0:31:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a treacherous heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.35,0:31:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and envy is insidious.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.44,0:31:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.78,0:31:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how envy\Nthreatens to disrupt peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.18,0:32:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.43,0:32:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad news?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.18,0:32:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s a sweetie.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.23,0:32:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It reminds me that I want to speak to her\Nabout a necklace.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.52,0:32:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You too?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.94,0:32:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t think she’s showing off?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.19,0:32:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.07,0:32:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone thinks she’s “Miss Wonderful”;
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.32,0:32:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,she’s starting to agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.70,0:32:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this just about Haley?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.75,0:32:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems it’s all about Haley.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.17,0:32:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Your tea is getting cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.55,0:32:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’re changing the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.59,0:32:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.63,0:32:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but you’ve brought this up before.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.51,0:32:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.52,0:33:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re friends; you pioneer together.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.31,0:33:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and that’s why I’m concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.40,0:33:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Concern is good,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.90,0:33:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.24,0:33:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is there just a little bit of envy in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.50,0:33:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.46,0:33:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Emily is suffering\Nfrom an onset of envy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.93,0:33:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice\Nhow she questioned Haley’s motives
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.60,0:33:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and potentially called\NHaley’s reputation into question?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.77,0:33:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It could happen to any one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.86,0:33:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So how do we battle and conquer envy?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.86,0:34:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,By cultivating two beautiful qualities,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.29,0:34:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,humility and contentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.33,0:34:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see what the Bible\Nhas to say about humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.21,0:34:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn with me, please,\Nto Philippians chapter 2,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.59,0:34:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re going to begin reading\Nin verse 3
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.55,0:34:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,—Philippians 2:3:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.43,0:34:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do nothing out of contentiousness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.85,0:34:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or out of egotism.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.48,0:34:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What is egotism?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.48,0:34:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s having\Nan exaggerated opinion of oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.49,0:34:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think that the religious leaders\Nin Jesus’ day,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.24,0:34:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph’s brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.79,0:34:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Korah, Dathan, and Abiram
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.50,0:34:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,had this affliction?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.50,0:34:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they have an exaggerated view\Nof themselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.84,0:34:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Without question!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.05,0:34:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s an affliction\Nthat could affect any one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.84,0:34:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the solution?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.85,0:35:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Paul continues:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.85,0:35:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“But with humility [or, lowliness of mind]
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.35,0:35:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,consider others superior to you”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.23,0:35:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,—or consider others
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.44,0:35:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,as more important than yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.82,0:35:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that kind of mindset
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.40,0:35:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,allows a person to do what’s stated\Nin verse 4:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.53,0:35:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“As you look out not only
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.62,0:35:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“for your own interests,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.79,0:35:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but also for the interests of others.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.71,0:35:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A humble person
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.13,0:35:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,looks out for others.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.55,0:35:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t feel that he deserves
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.97,0:35:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,more than others.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.35,0:35:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Contentment—a content person\Nis satisfied with what he has.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.81,0:35:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t compare\Nhis privilege or his possession
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.81,0:35:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,with another person’s privilege\Nor possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.15,0:35:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s content.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.61,0:36:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Humility, contentment
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.07,0:36:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,—with Jehovah’s help we can cultivate\Nthese beautiful qualities—
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.08,0:36:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,qualities that leave no room for envy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.08,0:36:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And in doing so, we promote peace
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.38,0:36:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,—inner peace, peace in our family,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.22,0:36:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and peace in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.43,0:36:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can be sure\Nthat Jehovah appreciates that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.39,0:36:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Gajus Glockentin,\Na helper to the Publishing Committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.27,0:36:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,will now present the next talk\Nof this symposium,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.82,0:36:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Put Away’ Peace Wreckers—Dishonesty.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.16,0:36:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What comes to your mind\Nwhen you hear the word “dishonesty”?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.33,0:36:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you think of Satan,\N“the father of the lie.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.13,0:36:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Or Ananias and his wife come to your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.01,0:37:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They lost their lives because of lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.05,0:37:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We do not want to imitate such ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.80,0:37:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We avoid lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.77,0:37:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that, though, as far as our honesty goes?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.85,0:37:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Our holy God, Jehovah,\Nwants us to be holy as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.53,0:37:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is why he urged\Nthe ancient Israelites
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.24,0:37:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,not to deceive others
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.45,0:37:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as mentioned at Leviticus 19:11.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.33,0:37:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this not add some color to honesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.58,0:37:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dishonesty includes\N(and please take note of this definition)
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.25,0:37:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,intentionally leading someone\Nto a wrong conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.68,0:37:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, by twisting the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.43,0:37:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or by providing only certain details,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.68,0:37:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we endanger our peace with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.35,0:37:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can we say so?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.40,0:37:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How does dishonesty wreck peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.78,0:38:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace and a peaceful relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.78,0:38:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,are built on trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.41,0:38:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Trusting someone makes you feel\Nsafe and secure
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.20,0:38:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and puts you at ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.66,0:38:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no peace without trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.50,0:38:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we develop trust?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.96,0:38:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust is the result\Nof spending time together,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.47,0:38:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,speaking the truth with one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.01,0:38:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We trust people who act unselfishly
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.14,0:38:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and do not use “crooked speech,”\Nas the Bible puts it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.85,0:38:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If someone deceives us only once\Nor is dishonest in another way,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.82,0:38:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we might start to question\Neverything they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.36,0:38:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,One single act of dishonesty may be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.36,0:38:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It can ruin their reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.41,0:38:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,As bad as this is,\Ndishonesty has the potential
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.46,0:38:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to create even greater damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.42,0:38:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Dishonesty can be compared
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.92,0:39:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with a highly contagious virus.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.51,0:39:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Dishonesty breeds dishonesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.39,0:39:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,People who have contact\Nwith deceitful, dishonest persons
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.47,0:39:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,are in danger of being infected.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.73,0:39:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Dishonesty might not only wreck\None relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.36,0:39:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but multiple relationships,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.40,0:39:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,putting the unity and peace\Nof the whole group at risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.62,0:39:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This reminds us of the relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.28,0:39:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,between Laban and Jacob\Nin the Bible book of Genesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.87,0:39:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on the agreement with Laban,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.71,0:39:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jacob worked hard for seven years
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.80,0:39:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to marry Laban’s daughter Rachel.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.88,0:39:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And despite this high price\Nthat Jacob had to pay,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.89,0:39:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,those years seemed for him
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.81,0:39:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,just like “a few days.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.60,0:39:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, instead of Rachel,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.19,0:40:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he received the older daughter, Leah,\Nas a wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.44,0:40:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So now Leah was also part of the deception.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.45,0:40:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the result after Jacob had found out
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.20,0:40:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that Laban tricked him?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.66,0:40:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The trust was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.16,0:40:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The relationship had suffered\Nto a great degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.08,0:40:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Dishonesty wrecked the peace\Nin those relationships,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.46,0:40:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and so the following seven years\Nof work for Rachel were bitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.51,0:40:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And Laban’s dishonesty emboldened him\Nto continue in his course.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.93,0:40:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He unfairly changed Jacob’s wages ten times.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.31,0:40:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He deceived Jacob.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.31,0:40:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of Laban’s dishonesty,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.94,0:40:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the peace in the whole family\Nwas disrupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.32,0:40:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us now continue to watch\Nthe next segment of the dramatization.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.20,0:40:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We left Emily and Celia sitting\Nin a coffee shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.37,0:40:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Please watch carefully, and notice
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.83,0:41:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,how Emily is tempted to alter the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.38,0:41:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You pioneer together.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.59,0:41:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, and that’s why I’m concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.51,0:41:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Concern is good,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.51,0:41:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.60,0:41:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is there just a little bit of envy in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.10,0:41:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you would understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.98,0:41:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I understand your feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.61,0:41:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But not about Haley?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.28,0:41:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven’t seen all her posts.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.74,0:41:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s nothing immoral, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.91,0:41:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.41,0:41:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. That’s not like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.37,0:41:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.79,0:41:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s a case of her being more careful\Nhow she comes across,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.92,0:41:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s another matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.96,0:41:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don’t you talk to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.47,0:41:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.93,0:42:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Emily, you are a beautiful, spiritual sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.61,0:42:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.78,0:42:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,for years,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.61,0:42:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a bad habit\Nof comparing myself to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.99,0:42:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,My own insecurity hurt me
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.75,0:42:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and my closest friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.97,0:42:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don’t think\NI should’ve spoken to Celia?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.89,0:42:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I’m glad you asked Celia about it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.39,0:42:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,—someone you trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.52,0:42:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What did she say?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.94,0:42:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she definitely understands how I feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.44,0:42:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.49,0:42:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And about Haley’s posts?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.66,0:42:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she hasn’t seen\Neverything she has out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.54,0:42:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.46,0:43:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She did say that Haley
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.79,0:43:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,needs to be more careful
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.21,0:43:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,how she comes across.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.97,0:43:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What did she suggest?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.10,0:43:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That I should tell her\Nthat she needs to stop,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.18,0:43:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but I’m too worked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.31,0:43:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Look,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.07,0:43:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,if Celia agrees\Nthat Haley is doing something she shouldn’t,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.61,0:43:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you should talk to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.70,0:43:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll find the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.26,0:43:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.80,0:43:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.80,0:43:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you say the prayer?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.26,0:43:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.68,0:44:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, we’d like to praise you
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.23,0:44:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for your generosity and kindness . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.86,0:44:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice how Emily just heard\Nwhat she wanted to hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.49,0:44:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In talking to her husband, Jake,\Nshe painted an incomplete picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.12,0:44:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,She did not relay that Celia had no opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.12,0:44:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,about the social media posts of Haley.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.04,0:44:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And contrary to what she told her husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.34,0:44:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Celia did not encourage her\Nto tell Haley to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.01,0:44:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters deserve the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.14,0:44:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But Emily didn’t relay that, did she?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.52,0:44:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,She was dishonest, something that can have
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.64,0:44:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a damaging effect, as we will see later.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.73,0:44:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah wants us to put away
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.94,0:44:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,this peace wrecker, dishonesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.11,0:44:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants us to always be truthful,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.16,0:44:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,even in small matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.62,0:45:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, how do we put away dishonesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.75,0:45:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us please turn to Ephesians chapter 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.50,0:45:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Here the apostle Paul reminds us
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.42,0:45:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of a reason to be honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.67,0:45:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Ephesians chapter 4,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.63,0:45:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and we want to read verse 25:
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.14,0:45:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, now that you\Nhave put away deceit,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.10,0:45:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“each one of you speak truth\Nwith his neighbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.48,0:45:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because we are members\Nbelonging to one another.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.15,0:45:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice why we put away deceit
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.61,0:45:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and speak truth with one another?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.74,0:45:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul says: “Because we are\Nmembers belonging to one another.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.16,0:45:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, Paul reminds us of the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.17,0:45:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that dishonesty affects others
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.92,0:45:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,—our brothers and our relationship with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.38,0:45:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, knowing this,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.63,0:46:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,how can we put away dishonesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.35,0:46:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is:
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.39,0:46:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,By considering the consequences\Nof dishonesty and honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.44,0:46:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This will help us to do the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.40,0:46:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what are the consequences of dishonesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.03,0:46:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As we’ve seen in the case of Laban and Jacob,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.49,0:46:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it will disrupt the peace with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.16,0:46:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And since Jehovah hates dishonesty,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.04,0:46:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it will also disrupt our peace with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.79,0:46:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.84,0:46:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,what are the consequences of honesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.01,0:46:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,While dishonesty might seem in the moment\Nto be the easier way out,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.30,0:46:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in the long run,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.35,0:46:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,honesty will enable us to have good friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.23,0:46:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They want to enjoy peace as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.27,0:46:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore they are also searching
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.15,0:46:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for someone they can trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.03,0:46:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this way, we are
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.03,0:47:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,like ‘body members belonging to one another.’
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.70,0:47:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And even more important,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.95,0:47:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we will enjoy a good conscience
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.58,0:47:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and “peace with God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.50,0:47:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us, therefore, put away\Nthis peace wrecker (dishonesty)
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.63,0:47:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,by sticking to the truth\Neven in small things.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.51,0:47:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear brothers and sisters, Jehovah knows
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.39,0:47:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that for us imperfect humans
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.60,0:47:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,this is not always easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.06,0:47:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, he promises to help us
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.81,0:47:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and to bless every step we take
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.86,0:47:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to build trust and peace
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.15,0:47:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and not to wreck it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.49,0:47:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Patrick LaFranca,\Na helper to the Personnel Committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.16,0:47:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,will now present\Nthe next talk of this symposium,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.33,0:47:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Put Away’ Peace Wreckers—Harmful Gossip.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.43,0:48:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you gossip?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.72,0:48:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.89,0:48:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, whenever we share\Nany news about others,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.14,0:48:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that is a form of gossip.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.27,0:48:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we are interested in others,\Nwe might say,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.52,0:48:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am really concerned\Nabout Brother Smith’s health,”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.77,0:48:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or “Did you hear about Sister Brown’s\Nexperience in the ministry?”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.36,0:48:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this type of gossip harmful?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.53,0:48:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally not.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.53,0:48:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, we need to be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.74,0:48:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,At 1 Timothy 5:13,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.87,0:48:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul spoke out against certain sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.62,0:48:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,who were “gossipers\Nand meddlers in other people’s affairs.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.59,0:48:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We do not need to know\Nand share everything we know
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.92,0:48:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,about what’s happening\Nin other people’s lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.59,0:48:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What if, for example,\NBrother Smith did not want others
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.10,0:48:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to know details about his health problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.31,0:48:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to respect the privacy of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.19,0:48:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Or what if talking\Nabout Sister Brown’s experience turns into,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.94,0:49:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“Oh, you know, she always brags\Nabout her success in the ministry.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.49,0:49:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When our talk about others turns negative,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.95,0:49:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,it can develop into slander.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.37,0:49:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Slander is making\Ndeliberate, false statements
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.91,0:49:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that damage another’s reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.21,0:49:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s now consider\Nhow harmful gossip wrecks peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.13,0:49:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have spread harmful gossip\Nabout someone and he hears about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.14,0:49:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see him the next time,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.93,0:49:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what will be the look on his face?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.97,0:49:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Please read with me Proverbs 25:23:
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.11,0:49:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“The north wind brings a downpour,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.82,0:49:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and a gossiping tongue brings an angry face.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.11,0:49:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The north wind in Palestine
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.87,0:49:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,brought dark clouds and rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.25,0:49:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, when the one you gossiped about
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.67,0:49:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,catches wind of this and he sees you,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.34,0:50:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,he will have a gloomy, angry face.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.51,0:50:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There will be a storm\Nand a chilled relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.26,0:50:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when that happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.51,0:50:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you may feel very badly and apologize,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.39,0:50:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but you may have damaged his reputation
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.27,0:50:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way that may be difficult to undo.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.98,0:50:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to this old Jewish story:
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.15,0:50:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,‘A man went about town\Nslandering the town’s wise man.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.16,0:50:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Later, the malicious gossiper\Nrealized his wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.41,0:50:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and went to the wise man\Nand asked for his forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.04,0:50:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He offered to do\Nwhatever was needed to make amends.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.13,0:50:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘The wise man made one request.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.00,0:50:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He told the gossiper\Nto take a feather pillow,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.72,0:50:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,‘cut it open,\Nand scatter the feathers to the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.18,0:50:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, the gossiper\Nwas puzzled by this request,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.31,0:50:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,‘but he did as instructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.73,0:50:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Then he returned to the wise man.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.06,0:51:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,‘“Am I now forgiven?” he asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.82,0:51:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,‘“First, go and gather all the feathers,”\Nthe wise man responded.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.40,0:51:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,‘“But, how can I?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.28,0:51:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,‘The wind has already scattered them.”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.28,0:51:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,‘The wise man replied,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.29,0:51:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,‘“It is as difficult to repair\Nthe damage done by your words
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.08,0:51:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is to recover the feathers.”’
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.79,0:51:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, once spoken,\Nhurtful words cannot be retrieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.80,0:51:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s not scatter feathers in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.09,0:51:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If we spread rumors,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.18,0:51:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it can seriously disturb\Nthe peace of many in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.93,0:51:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We find an example of this
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.94,0:51:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,at Acts 21:20, 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.27,0:51:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The older men of the Jerusalem congregation\Nexplained to Paul
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.90,0:51:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that some Jews\Nhad spread a rumor among Jewish Christians
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.45,0:51:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that he had been teaching an apostasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.58,0:51:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,speaking against the Law of Moses.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.25,0:52:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, this was a twisting of the facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.96,0:52:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul never spoke disrespectfully of the Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.21,0:52:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He even went to synagogues
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.22,0:52:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,where he reasoned\Non the basis of the Hebrew Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.89,0:52:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Such stories could have led\Nsome newly converted Jewish Christians
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.89,0:52:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to think that Paul\Ndid not respect God’s arrangements,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.81,0:52:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and this could have seriously disrupted\Nthe peace of the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.65,0:52:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.94,0:52:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,notice the effect\Nthat harmful gossip can have
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.11,0:52:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,on the peace in a congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.04,0:52:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you believe that?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.70,0:52:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially as a pioneer,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.12,0:52:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of example is she setting?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.12,0:52:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Has Emily stopped following her?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.34,0:52:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not yet, but she probably will.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.84,0:52:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Alistair, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.30,0:52:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.47,0:52:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Haley’s posts on QuicPost.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.80,0:52:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.18,0:52:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Emily has told me
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.22,0:53:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,they’re all just, “Look at me
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.27,0:53:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,—my clothes, my hair, my makeup.”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.90,0:53:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And even Celia agrees with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.48,0:53:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s very easy to take things\Nout of context on social media.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.86,0:53:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that I’ve done that and realized later
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.54,0:53:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.04,0:53:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that’s a good point.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.33,0:53:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I don’t want to pull you away,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.71,0:53:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you have a minute, would you mind\Ngiving me a hand with these boxes?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.13,0:53:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.81,0:53:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.19,0:53:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.98,0:53:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jake, back in the hall,\NI know you were just expressing concern,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.98,0:53:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but here’s something to consider.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.61,0:53:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This principle is one of my favorites.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.32,0:53:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s found at Proverbs
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.12,0:54:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,chapter 18 and verse 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.25,0:54:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“The first to state his case seems right,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.67,0:54:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,until the other party comes\Nand cross-examines him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.68,0:54:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not sure I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.51,0:54:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It just means that sometimes
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.31,0:54:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we only hear one side of a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.85,0:54:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And until we personally hear both,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.23,0:54:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s best not to draw any conclusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.36,0:54:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And even then, if it’s something negative,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.61,0:54:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we wouldn’t want to spread it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.66,0:54:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,any more than we’d want something spread\Nabout ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.92,0:54:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I hadn’t considered that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.92,0:54:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.71,0:54:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to apologize to Harry and Marie
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.63,0:54:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and have Emily talk directly to Haley.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.18,0:55:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.98,0:55:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice what Jake said
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.23,0:55:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,after the elder graciously helped him reason
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.28,0:55:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,on Proverbs 18:17?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.03,0:55:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, “I had not considered that.”
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.70,0:55:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Jake just did not stop and think
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.08,0:55:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,before he said\Nthose negative things about Haley.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.96,0:55:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can we “put away” harmful gossip
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.42,0:55:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,before it begins?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.42,0:55:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read Proverbs 15:28:
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.09,0:55:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“The heart of the righteous one\Nmeditates before answering,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.60,0:55:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“but the mouth of the wicked
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.60,0:55:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,blurts out bad things.”
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.40,0:55:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So before we say bad things about others,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.03,0:55:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to meditate.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.03,0:55:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No, this does not mean\Na long-drawn-out process.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.61,0:56:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It just requires a little thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.03,0:56:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What thoughts could have stopped Jake
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.16,0:56:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from repeating his wife’s negative view\Nof Haley’s post?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.17,0:56:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have asked himself:
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.42,0:56:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Is what I am about to say true?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.71,0:56:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Is it kind, loving?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.84,0:56:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How will Harry and Marie view Haley
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.35,0:56:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,if they hear\Nthose negative things about her?’
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.64,0:56:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Another principle\Nthat will help us to put away harmful gossip
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.81,0:56:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is the so-called Golden Rule,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.44,0:56:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as recorded at Luke 6:31.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.19,0:56:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said: “Just as you\Nwant men to do to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.87,0:56:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,do the same way to them.”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.78,0:56:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This means showing empathy,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.25,0:56:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,putting ourselves\Nin the place of the other person,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.87,0:56:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and asking ourselves,\N‘How would I feel
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.17,0:56:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,if someone said this about me?’
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.63,0:57:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,One situation that may tempt us\Nto engage in harmful gossip
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.43,0:57:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is when we believe we\Nhave been wronged by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.31,0:57:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of applying the counsel
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.39,0:57:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,at Matthew 5:23, 24
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.23,0:57:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and 18:15
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.98,0:57:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk to the person privately,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.27,0:57:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we could start talking about it\Nto others who are not involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.95,0:57:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine if after finally talking\Nwith the person
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.83,0:57:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you find out he actually\Ndid not wrong you at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.00,0:57:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You will have made the situation much worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.79,0:57:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But whether we are right or wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.13,0:57:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,engaging in hurtful speech
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.71,0:57:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,will never improve a situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.55,0:57:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Gossip requires a speaker and a listener.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.31,0:57:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it wrong to listen to harmful gossip?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.93,0:57:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.48,0:57:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Note what Proverbs 17:4 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.27,0:58:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“A wicked man pays attention\Nto hurtful speech,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.28,0:58:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and a deceptive man\Nlistens to a malicious tongue.”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.16,0:58:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.16,0:58:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In God’s eyes if we listen to hurtful,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.08,0:58:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,malicious speech, we too\Nbear a heavy responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.96,0:58:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,By listening to the gossiper,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.96,0:58:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we are encouraging him to go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.26,0:58:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what should you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.55,0:58:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Without taking on an air\Nof self-righteousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.64,0:58:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you could simply say,\N“Let’s change the subject,”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.18,0:58:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or “I don’t really feel comfortable\Ntalking about this;
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.11,0:58:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,after all, she is not here\Nto defend herself.”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.90,0:58:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we find that a brother or sister
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.07,0:58:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,likes to gossip,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.58,0:58:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we may find it easier to avoid harmful gossip
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.91,0:58:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,by stopping close association\Nwith that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.54,0:58:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 20:19 frankly counsels:
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.63,0:59:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not associate\Nwith one who loves to gossip.”
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.26,0:59:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, dear friends,\Nlet’s put away harmful gossip.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.10,0:59:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing so, we will maintain
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.43,0:59:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,our precious peace and unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.69,0:59:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Kenneth Cook,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.69,0:59:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a member of the Governing Body,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.77,0:59:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,will now present\Nthe final talk of this symposium,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.24,0:59:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Put Away’ Peace Wreckers\N—Uncontrolled Anger.”
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.67,0:59:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan is the main peace wrecker.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.63,0:59:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The Scriptures tell us\Nthat he is driven by “great anger.”
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.59,0:59:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,His anger is malicious and uncontrolled.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.76,0:59:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Would any sound-minded,\NGod-fearing person
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.68,0:59:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,allow himself\Nto reflect Satan’s vicious anger?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.14,0:59:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.14,0:59:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why all true servants of God\Nare determined
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.06,1:00:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to “put away” uncontrolled anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.78,1:00:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But apart from uncontrolled anger,\Nis all anger bad?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.40,1:00:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible does not condemn all anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.87,1:00:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It teaches us that anger is wrong\Nwhen it is uncontrolled or unjustified.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.87,1:00:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,At Ephesians 4:26, God’s Word tells us:
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.50,1:00:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be wrathful, but [it adds] do not sin.”
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.25,1:00:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, anger\Nmay simply be a strong feeling
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.42,1:00:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes into us\Nbecause of being upset or annoyed
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.14,1:00:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,by something that we see as being wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.39,1:00:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That in itself is not bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.60,1:00:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But what makes anger bad\Nis when it fills a person’s heart
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.11,1:00:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and he or she just loses control of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.11,1:00:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When that happens,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.11,1:00:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it may cause a person\Nto act without a sound mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.61,1:00:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who continue to lash out in anger\Nwill not gain salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.45,1:00:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Galatians 5:20 lists “fits of anger”
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.87,1:01:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,among “the works of the flesh”\Nthat will prevent a person
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.29,1:01:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,from inheriting God’s Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.59,1:01:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There will be no place\Nfor such ones in God’s new world.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.88,1:01:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A brief review of how uncontrolled anger
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.68,1:01:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,wrecks peace for ourselves and others
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.18,1:01:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,will highlight why this is so.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.93,1:01:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncontrolled anger
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.94,1:01:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,harms both the angry person\Nas well as those around him.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.31,1:01:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We read at Proverbs 29:22
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.32,1:01:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that an angry person “stirs up strife,”
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.36,1:01:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,adding that he “commits many transgressions.”
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.37,1:01:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,One of these many sins is abusive speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.04,1:01:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We must work to show restraint\Nwhen speaking with workmates,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.21,1:01:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with strangers in the ministry,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.46,1:01:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with our brothers and sisters\Nin the congregation,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.92,1:01:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and with our family members.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.13,1:01:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad feelings must be controlled.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.59,1:01:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Abusive speech, ridicule, contempt,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.72,1:01:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and hateful anger are wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.52,1:02:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Giving vent to such feelings\Ncan destroy precious friendships
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.65,1:02:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with other people and with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.78,1:02:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t be like a volcano\Nthat will not quiet down.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.90,1:02:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like an erupting volcano\Nwill harm those living around it,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.66,1:02:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,so too a person who expresses intense anger
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.08,1:02:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,will harm those living around him.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.00,1:02:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He also damages himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.46,1:02:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In what way?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.46,1:02:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Acting on anger often leads\Nto even more aggression,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.42,1:02:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so uncontrolled anger\Ncan also affect our own peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.64,1:02:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It can cause us to do something\Nthat we will later regret.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.27,1:02:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It can have a negative effect on our health.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.39,1:02:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Medical studies show that uncontrolled anger
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.65,1:02:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,can cause high blood pressure\Nand respiratory problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.53,1:02:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It can also affect the liver and pancreas,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.36,1:02:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and such anger can cause digestive problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.16,1:02:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When a person becomes angry,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.49,1:02:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,he or she will not always think clearly.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.29,1:03:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,After a fit of rage,\Na person may become depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.04,1:03:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder we read at Proverbs 14:30
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.88,1:03:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that “a calm heart gives life to the body.”
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.80,1:03:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The disastrous consequences\Nof uncontrolled anger
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.56,1:03:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,are illustrated in God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.85,1:03:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,by the actions of Simeon and Levi,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.19,1:03:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,sons of the patriarch Jacob.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.86,1:03:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When they learned that their sister, Dinah,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.11,1:03:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,was violated by a man named Shechem,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.07,1:03:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we read at Genesis 34:7
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.20,1:03:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that “they were offended and very angry.”
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.03,1:03:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, they had a valid reason to be angry,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.54,1:03:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but they took their anger too far.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.25,1:03:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It was uncontrolled.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.25,1:03:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Simeon and Levi\Ntook vengeance on Shechem.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.67,1:03:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Using deception, they attacked and killed
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.30,1:03:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,every male in Shechem’s city.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.97,1:03:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, along with the other sons of Jacob,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.22,1:04:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they plundered it and took\Nthe women and little children captive.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.06,1:04:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Dinah’s tragic experience\Nmust have grieved Jacob greatly.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.06,1:04:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, he condemned\Nhis sons’ uncontrolled anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.61,1:04:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Simeon and Levi\Ntried to justify their actions,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.11,1:04:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but that was not the end of the matter,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.20,1:04:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because Jehovah was also displeased.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.70,1:04:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,For this reason, Jacob later foretold
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.17,1:04:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that the descendants of Simeon and Levi
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.79,1:04:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,were to be scattered\Namong the tribes of Israel.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.09,1:04:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Their uncontrolled anger brought disfavor
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.43,1:04:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,from God and from their father, Jacob.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.39,1:04:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re wise to pay attention\Nto such Scriptural accounts
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.23,1:04:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and put away uncontrolled anger\Nand all of the harm that it brings.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.98,1:04:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.23,1:04:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how a person\Nmight be tempted to give in to anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.00,1:05:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Nana?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.91,1:05:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t forget eggs, dear.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.00,1:05:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, I didn’t forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.29,1:05:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure, love?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.38,1:05:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I won’t forget. OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.54,1:05:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.13,1:05:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. Love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.13,1:05:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.14,1:05:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.39,1:05:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Haley, finally, I’ve caught you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.94,1:05:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a minute?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.61,1:05:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Emily.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.57,1:05:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we talk later?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.23,1:05:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m really struggling this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.82,1:05:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it’s just that you’ve been so busy,\Nand I’ve been waiting for the right moment;
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.74,1:05:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d really just like to address it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.41,1:05:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. What’s up?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.21,1:05:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just that I’ve noticed\Nyour posts lately on QuicPost.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.75,1:05:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What about them?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.42,1:05:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, do you really think they’re something\Nthat a pioneer should be posting?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.97,1:05:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.59,1:06:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people might think you’re bragging.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.35,1:06:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people? What people?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.60,1:06:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a business account.\NI’ve got to show off my products.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.93,1:06:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. I get that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.64,1:06:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just—\NI don’t know.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.77,1:06:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It could feel like you’re drawing\Na little too much attention to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.65,1:06:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would think like that? You?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.36,1:06:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not just me; Celia felt the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.24,1:06:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You spoke to Celia about this?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.70,1:06:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t want to upset you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.20,1:06:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Jake said that I needed to take . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.49,1:06:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Jake! So everyone thinks\Nmy posts are inappropriate?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.62,1:06:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everyone, Haley.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.92,1:06:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not what I am saying at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.42,1:06:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You are such . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.25,1:06:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! I can’t believe you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.92,1:06:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Who else have you spoken to?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.30,1:06:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You are just such a gossip!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.38,1:06:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not gossiping. I was trying to . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.59,1:06:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You are!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.51,1:06:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m just trying to help you,\Nif you would just listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.76,1:06:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re so jealous!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.72,1:06:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’d just listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.52,1:06:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, listen to this.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.27,1:06:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And I expected more from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.69,1:06:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Haley, what are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.98,1:06:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Gossiping about my posts!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.36,1:06:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you that lonely\Nthat you’ve got nothing better to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.74,1:07:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Haley,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.33,1:07:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,wait, please!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.01,1:07:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you left feeling a bit tense?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.76,1:07:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, you know\Nwhat uncontrolled anger can lead to.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.31,1:07:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we’ve defined uncontrolled anger
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.02,1:07:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and considered what it can lead to,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.61,1:07:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the next question is,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.61,1:07:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we put away uncontrolled anger?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.86,1:07:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we need to recognize\Nthe danger of uncontrolled anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.62,1:07:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 25:28 states
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.37,1:07:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that “as a city broken through,\Nwithout a wall,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.75,1:07:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is the man who cannot control his temper.”
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.92,1:07:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Strong city walls\Nwere vital in ancient times.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.84,1:08:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Without them a city\Nwould quickly fall to invaders;
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.97,1:08:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,likewise, so will those\Nwho cannot control their temper.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.22,1:08:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,By losing control, they\Nmake themselves vulnerable
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.19,1:08:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to the invasion of wrong thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.15,1:08:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,—thoughts that can cause them\Nto hurt themselves and others.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.23,1:08:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Uncontrolled anger can do just that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.36,1:08:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, after recognizing the danger,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.53,1:08:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we must pause and then deal with the anger
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.08,1:08:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,before it causes us\Nto do something that we will regret.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.92,1:08:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When anger grows within us,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.92,1:08:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re wise to recall\Nwhat happened with Simeon and Levi.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.80,1:08:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We might also recall what happened
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.09,1:08:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in the video dramatization\Nthat we just viewed.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.72,1:08:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, in each case,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.93,1:08:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,pausing before reacting out of anger
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.02,1:08:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,may have spared\Nmuch pain and heartache, true?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.44,1:08:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why we have this warning
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.44,1:08:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,at Proverbs 17:14:
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.40,1:09:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“Before the quarrel breaks out,\Ntake your leave.”
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.32,1:09:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,With that in mind,\Neach of us should ask himself:
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.45,1:09:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Do I tend to jump to conclusions
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.03,1:09:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,‘when I don’t have all the facts?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.25,1:09:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,‘If so, can I take my leave\Nand put away anger
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.29,1:09:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,before it starts to build up?’
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.71,1:09:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The inspired advice
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.71,1:09:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,found at James 1:19 will help us to do so
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.13,1:09:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,—but only if we make\Na sincere and determined effort
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.39,1:09:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to apply what it says.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.77,1:09:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read that verse—James 1:19.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.73,1:09:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we find some simple steps
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.19,1:09:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to help us put away uncontrolled anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.15,1:09:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “Know this, my beloved brothers:
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.95,1:09:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Everyone must be quick to listen,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.57,1:09:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,slow to speak, slow to anger.”
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.87,1:09:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If we ask Jehovah to help us with this,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.33,1:09:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,namely to “be quick to listen,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.75,1:10:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,slow to speak, slow to anger,”
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.59,1:10:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,he will assist us to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.63,1:10:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He will help us\Nto see the facts of the matter,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.59,1:10:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,show understanding,\Nand then put away uncontrolled anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.35,1:10:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A word of caution, though:
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.48,1:10:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,To succeed in doing our part,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.15,1:10:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we must choose our associates wisely.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.27,1:10:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We could undermine all of our good work
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.99,1:10:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah’s help in controlling our anger
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.61,1:10:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,if we choose associates who are arrogant,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.78,1:10:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,opinionated, or quick to become angry.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.79,1:10:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Regarding someone who is disposed to rage,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.96,1:10:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 22:25 warns:
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.67,1:10:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“Never learn his ways.”
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.05,1:10:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’ve enjoyed\Nanother outstanding series of talks
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.26,1:10:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that should help us to keep awake,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.39,1:10:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,maintain fine conduct,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.52,1:10:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and escape the judgment\Nthat will soon come on this world.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.77,1:10:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As this symposium has emphasized,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.44,1:11:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we must do our utmost\Nto continue to put away peace wreckers
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.61,1:11:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,such as inappropriate boasting, envy,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.03,1:11:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,dishonesty, harmful gossip,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.91,1:11:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and uncontrolled anger.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.49,1:11:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If we have a problem\Nwith any of the peacemaking qualities
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.04,1:11:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have discussed in this symposium,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.46,1:11:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,seek Jehovah’s help\Nto change and then work at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.46,1:11:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Our sincere efforts to pursue peace
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.42,1:11:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with our brothers and our sisters
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.76,1:11:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,will influence how earnestly\Nwe are awaiting “Jehovah’s day”
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.31,1:11:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and his promised new world.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.68,1:11:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, our genuine efforts\Nwill affect our hearts
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.65,1:11:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and will be noticed by our heavenly Father.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.77,1:11:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, in his great mercy,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.03,1:11:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will consider us\Nto be, as his Word says,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.95,1:11:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“spotless and unblemished and in peace”
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.24,1:11:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,—both with him\Nand with our fellow worshippers.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.04,1:12:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, brothers, for helping us\Nto strengthen our bond of unity.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.46,1:12:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the rebellion in Eden,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.88,1:12:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,peace among mankind as a whole\Nhas been lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.26,1:12:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite this, Jehovah has given peace
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.06,1:12:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to those who trust in him.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.10,1:12:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,How has he done so in the past,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.27,1:12:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and how does this strengthen\Nour faith in him today?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.36,1:12:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We invite you to enjoy Part 1\Nof the documentary
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.45,1:12:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{s16}{nArial}Jehovah Guides Us in the Way of Peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.01,1:12:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our military forces are committed to peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.47,1:12:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We have chosen peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.81,1:12:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Our wish, our prayer, is for peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.81,1:13:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We yearn for peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.35,1:13:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We pray for peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.99,1:13:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For thousands
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.36,1:13:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of years, humans have tried
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.70,1:13:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to find peace
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.25,1:13:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,—peace as individuals,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.13,1:13:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,peace as families,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.51,1:13:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,peace for the entire human race.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.60,1:13:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to lay the foundation of peace\Nfor generations to come.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.27,1:13:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to do the hard work now
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.64,1:13:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so our children and our grandchildren\Ncan grow up in a peaceful world.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.48,1:13:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The future we want:
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.95,1:13:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,opportunity and security for our families,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.12,1:13:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a rising standard of living,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.70,1:14:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,a sustainable, peaceful planet for our kids
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.21,1:14:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,—all that is within our reach.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.18,1:14:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, despite humans’ best efforts,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.64,1:14:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,peace
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.73,1:14:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,has been elusive.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.96,1:14:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,For millenniums,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.96,1:14:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,rulers and governments\Nhave tried to achieve peace
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.21,1:14:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,through treaties,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.50,1:14:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,resolutions,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.05,1:14:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,summits
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.42,1:14:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and, ironically, war.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.85,1:15:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Our peace as humans\Nis more fragile than ever.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.02,1:15:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Man’s efforts to bring about lasting peace
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.73,1:15:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,have failed time and time again.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.66,1:15:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn’t surprising to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.37,1:15:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah 10:23 tells us:
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.08,1:15:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“It does not belong to man . . .\Nto direct his step.”
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.75,1:15:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans were simply not designed\Nto rule themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.88,1:15:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Good health, safety, overall well-being
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.68,1:15:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,—these are becoming harder to find
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.59,1:15:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,as we move further into what the Bible
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.39,1:15:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,refers to as “the last days.”
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.47,1:15:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as human rule continues,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.39,1:15:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,disunity will continue.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.10,1:15:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true that global peace
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.40,1:15:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be obtained by human efforts alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.53,1:15:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But those who are close to God
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.45,1:15:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,can find peace of mind right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.07,1:16:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah 48:17, 18 says:
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.41,1:16:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“I, Jehovah, am your God,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.16,1:16:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“the One teaching you to benefit yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.62,1:16:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“the One guiding you
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.21,1:16:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the way you should walk.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.09,1:16:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“If only you would pay attention
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.46,1:16:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“to my commandments!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.30,1:16:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then your peace
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.97,1:16:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,would become just like a river.”
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.43,1:16:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s only Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.64,1:16:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,who has the ability to guide humans
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.93,1:16:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to real, lasting peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.48,1:16:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He promises he will bring this about.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.73,1:16:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Until this happens,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.77,1:16:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah continues to provide ways
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.82,1:16:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,for us to experience peace now.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.11,1:16:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How does he do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.03,1:16:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,By giving us “the peace of God\Nthat surpasses all understanding.”
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.46,1:16:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We aren’t the only ones\Nwhose peace has been challenged.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.13,1:17:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s Word is filled\Nwith accounts of faithful servants
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.35,1:17:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,whose peace was challenged
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.39,1:17:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,by the dominating forces of their day.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.81,1:17:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,As we study and meditate on these accounts,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.23,1:17:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the lessons we learn from them
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.61,1:17:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,help us to trust in Jehovah\Nas he guides us to peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.65,1:17:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Understanding how these accounts\Nrelate to Jehovah’s purpose to bring peace
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.82,1:17:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,by means of his Messianic Kingdom\Ngives us confidence
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.29,1:17:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that his purpose never fails
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.45,1:17:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will support\Nand guide us on into the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.75,1:17:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,One of Jehovah’s prophets
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.42,1:17:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,who learned this lesson firsthand was Jonah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.01,1:17:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah lived in the ninth century B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.59,1:17:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah assigned Jonah to go to Nineveh,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.97,1:17:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a city of the Assyrian Empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.18,1:17:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on what he knew about Nineveh,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.60,1:17:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah considered this to be
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.23,1:17:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,an intimidating and threatening assignment.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.31,1:17:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The Assyrians were known as fierce warriors,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.32,1:17:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and Nineveh itself was later described
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.74,1:18:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as a “city of bloodshed.”
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.82,1:18:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can understand Jonah’s trepidation\Nwhen Jehovah asks him
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.28,1:18:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to proclaim a judgment message
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.41,1:18:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,against this imposing city
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.41,1:18:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and its pagan inhabitants.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.92,1:18:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In an attempt to find peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.71,1:18:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah decides to go far away from Nineveh
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.09,1:18:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and boards a boat headed for Tarshish.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.97,1:18:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Tarshish is generally associated
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.81,1:18:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,with modern-day Spain.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.56,1:18:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So from Israel,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.15,1:18:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the complete opposite direction
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.02,1:18:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of Nineveh.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.78,1:18:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah found anything but peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.99,1:18:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.84,1:18:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,By the gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.34,1:18:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Furl the sail!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.47,1:19:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this was no ordinary storm.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.43,1:19:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so severe that the ship
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.64,1:19:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,was in danger of being wrecked.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.31,1:19:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, we’re taking on too much water!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.02,1:19:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This storm is from the gods!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.53,1:19:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Baal!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.03,1:19:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Eshmun!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.36,1:19:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The crew cried out to their gods,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.87,1:19:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jonah knew the true Source of the storm.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.24,1:19:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And now he accepts
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.00,1:19:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,personal responsibility for the situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.67,1:19:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lift me up
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.00,1:19:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and throw me into the sea,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.79,1:19:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and the sea will calm down for you;
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.67,1:19:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,for I know that it’s because of me
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.34,1:19:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that this violent storm has come upon you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.43,1:19:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine the courage it took
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.68,1:19:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jonah to make this request?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.43,1:19:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He had no way of knowing\Nif Jehovah would save him,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.06,1:19:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but he did not want others\Nto perish on his account.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.45,1:20:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In his mercy, Jehovah spares Jonah’s life.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.54,1:20:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How am I still alive?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.88,1:20:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What will become of me?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.80,1:20:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When faced
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.26,1:20:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with a difficult assignment,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.46,1:20:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah “got up to run away from Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.68,1:20:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to Tarshish.”
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.89,1:20:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah’s conscience had to bother him;
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.31,1:20:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,he had to be questioning his decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.85,1:20:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He tried to take matters into his own hands,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.27,1:20:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,tried to find his own peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.06,1:20:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does he find himself?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.07,1:20:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In the belly of a fish!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.11,1:20:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet he calls to Jehovah\Nin a moment of despair.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.41,1:20:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.16,1:20:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the depths of the Grave,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.87,1:20:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I cry to you for help.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.92,1:21:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Please hear my voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.26,1:21:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What I have vowed, I will pay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.39,1:21:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah could have reasoned
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.80,1:21:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that this was the end\Nof his assignment as Jehovah’s prophet.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.73,1:21:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, he did disobey direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.57,1:21:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So likely, he was surprised
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.86,1:21:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to hear the word of Jehovah come to him
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.15,1:21:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,a second time.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.08,1:21:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.21,1:21:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Get up,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.25,1:21:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,go to Nineveh the great city,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.54,1:21:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and proclaim to her
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.38,1:21:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the message that I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.93,1:21:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.51,1:21:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.10,1:21:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.69,1:22:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, Jonah trusted in himself
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.56,1:22:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and didn’t understand
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.32,1:22:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah would protect him\Nfrom the violent Assyrians.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.82,1:22:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But after being given\Na second chance, what happens?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.41,1:22:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then he puts aside
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.07,1:22:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,his human concerns
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.66,1:22:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and looks to Jehovah for protection.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.84,1:22:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In just 40 days more,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.59,1:22:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineveh will be overthrown.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.89,1:22:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, the true God, has spoken.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.18,1:22:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This city will be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.89,1:22:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineveh will be overthrown.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.31,1:22:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The true God will overthrow Nineveh.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.36,1:22:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The true God has spoken.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.32,1:22:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, the king himself repents
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.36,1:22:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and orders everyone
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.70,1:22:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in Nineveh to do the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.03,1:22:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah learned a valuable lesson
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.91,1:22:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,from this experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.54,1:22:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,By originally running away from Nineveh,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.83,1:23:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,he chose to trust in himself
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.63,1:23:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than putting his trust in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.80,1:23:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you Jonah?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.88,1:23:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.55,1:23:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy says you saved us.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.43,1:23:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Jehovah saved you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.06,1:23:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just—I was just a messenger.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.61,1:23:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah learned
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.48,1:23:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that without a doubt
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.07,1:23:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah protects those\Nwho trust and obey Him.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.11,1:23:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If Jehovah has asked you to do something,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.32,1:23:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,if he’s asked me to do something,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.53,1:23:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,if he’s leading us,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.74,1:23:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,he absolutely will guide us through it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.12,1:23:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah’s account proves this.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.13,1:23:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Although the Ninevites were spared
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.67,1:23:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because they repented (that’s true),
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.55,1:23:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Assyria later
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.59,1:23:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,returned to its evil, wicked ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.85,1:23:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,About a century
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.35,1:23:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,after Jonah’s judgment message,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.47,1:24:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,King Sennacherib of Assyria brought
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.23,1:24:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,his armies against the cities of Judah,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.77,1:24:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,including the city he wanted most
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.86,1:24:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.49,1:24:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,King Hezekiah of Judah
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.32,1:24:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,was an outstanding king
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.91,1:24:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,who “held fast to Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.37,1:24:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,From the beginning of his reign,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.62,1:24:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,he proved to be zealous for true worship
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.91,1:24:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,not only in Judah but in all of Israel.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.12,1:24:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hezekiah had done so much\Nto stand up for pure worship,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.17,1:24:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,yet now he is faced with the prospect
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.63,1:24:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of a siege against Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.38,1:24:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,by Sennacherib’s armies.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.93,1:24:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hezekiah agrees to pay Sennacherib
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.02,1:24:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a tribute in return for peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.27,1:24:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, the armies continue their conquests,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.86,1:24:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,as Sennacherib and his men besiege
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.11,1:24:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the strongly fortified city of Lachish.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.16,1:24:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,From here,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.24,1:24:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sennacherib sends a part of his army
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.33,1:25:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as military chiefs to Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.00,1:25:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in an attempt to demand surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.71,1:25:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The spokesman for the group was the Rabshakeh,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.79,1:25:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,who spoke Hebrew fluently.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.96,1:25:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He loudly ridiculed Hezekiah
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.76,1:25:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and taunted Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.76,1:25:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,boasting that Jehovah\Nwas no match against King Sennacherib.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.60,1:25:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine what these soldiers
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.64,1:25:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,must have been thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.93,1:25:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Sennacherib’s armies were on a warpath,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.98,1:25:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,taking city after city.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.06,1:25:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,To Hezekiah, this was a defining moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.40,1:25:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He had to decide if he would trust in himself
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.49,1:25:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or trust in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.99,1:25:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My brothers,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.37,1:25:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we must remember that Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.66,1:25:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is fully able to rescue us,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.75,1:25:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,just as he has in times past.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.21,1:25:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s Word . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.88,1:25:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,King Hezekiah,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.96,1:25:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,will you not even now face the facts?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.76,1:25:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We are trapped!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.26,1:25:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The Assyrians are at our gate,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.30,1:25:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and you cling to the belief
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.68,1:26:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that nothing bad will happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.14,1:26:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You will destroy everything
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.02,1:26:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you so hope to preserve
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.35,1:26:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,—the temple, Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.35,1:26:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,our very lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.44,1:26:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Shebna, I am not blind
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.27,1:26:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to the dangers that we face.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.52,1:26:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I too am afraid.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.69,1:26:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But if Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.24,1:26:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,allows Jerusalem to fall,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.32,1:26:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so be it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.11,1:26:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we give up what belongs to Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.04,1:26:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So as a man of faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.79,1:26:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hezekiah focused on Jehovah’s ability
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.21,1:26:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to save His people
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.88,1:26:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,despite Sennacherib’s\Ncontinued advances toward Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.26,1:26:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m curious about this king of yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.05,1:26:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Who does he think
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.64,1:26:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,will come to save him from me?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.81,1:26:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, your God,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.60,1:26:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is weak!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.06,1:26:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He will cringe before my god Asshur.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.20,1:26:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hezekiah remained
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.70,1:27:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,determined to trust in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.04,1:27:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This decision required\Na tremendous amount of faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.50,1:27:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,especially with more than
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.17,1:27:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,185,000 Assyrian soldiers
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.67,1:27:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,headed toward Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.26,1:27:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of trusting in himself,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.47,1:27:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,he continued to look
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.14,1:27:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah as the Source of true peace
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.56,1:27:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,even as an attack seemed imminent.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.24,1:27:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah again
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.28,1:27:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,showed just how insignificant
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.74,1:27:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,human rulers are in comparison to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.72,1:28:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hezekiah learned
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.72,1:28:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that when a way out seems impossible,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.02,1:28:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,trusting in Jehovah always leads to success.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.85,1:28:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah rewarded that trust\Nwith victory over the Assyrians.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.69,1:28:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a lesson\Nwe can apply now and in the near future.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.99,1:28:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There may be situations\Nwhen true worshippers seem trapped,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.20,1:28:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but never forget\Nthat Jehovah is all-powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.66,1:28:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s leading his people,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.79,1:28:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can follow\Nhis guidance with full confidence.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.09,1:28:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will protect those\Nwho trust in him at Armageddon.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.63,1:28:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerusalem remained safe
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.13,1:28:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,against attack for the time being,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.39,1:28:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but peaceful conditions didn’t last long.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.64,1:28:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hezekiah’s son Manasseh
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.89,1:28:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,did what was detestable
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.94,1:28:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in the eyes of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.27,1:28:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He brought back Baal worship
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.69,1:28:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and personally took its vilest practices
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.57,1:29:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to extremes,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.15,1:29:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,even putting a carved image of a false god
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.36,1:29:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,right inside Jehovah’s temple.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.03,1:29:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you have a king
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.37,1:29:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,who’s supposed to be protecting\Nthe people from idolatrous influence
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.25,1:29:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,doing the exact opposite\N—building altars to false gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.21,1:29:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He even went so far\Nas to pass his own sons through the fire,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.09,1:29:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,sacrificing them to these gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.42,1:29:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The peace with God that Hezekiah
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.80,1:29:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,worked so hard to achieve for the nation
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.51,1:29:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is now reversed by the actions of his son.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.31,1:29:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.52,1:29:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah punished Manasseh severely.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.81,1:29:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He allowed the king of Assyria
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.86,1:29:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to take him captive to Babylon.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.32,1:29:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,While in captivity,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.44,1:29:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Manasseh ultimately repented.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.90,1:29:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He humbled himself,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.91,1:29:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and he stayed faithful
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.91,1:29:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,right to the end of his life.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.33,1:29:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.37,1:29:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We can imagine him impressing
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.91,1:29:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the importance of faithfulness
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.87,1:29:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah on his young grandson Josiah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.92,1:29:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.96,1:30:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is holy,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.63,1:30:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and you must serve him
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.22,1:30:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the way he wants us to.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.51,1:30:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All other gods
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.31,1:30:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,are powerless.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.44,1:30:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, in spite of all this,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.15,1:30:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the people still thought
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.90,1:30:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that they could serve Jehovah and Baal.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.99,1:30:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So after becoming king,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.74,1:30:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah started a campaign against idolatry.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.16,1:30:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve seen these cheaper.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.16,1:30:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Take it or leave it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.88,1:30:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We start here!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.93,1:30:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.19,1:31:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what we will do to every false god in the land.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.28,1:31:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He tore down altars used for false worship,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.16,1:31:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,sacred poles, images, and statues.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.20,1:31:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He was intent \Non cleansing the land of idolatry.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.29,1:31:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, he showed remarkable courage
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.12,1:31:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to stand up for true worship\Nat a time when few were doing so.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.05,1:31:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no doubt this was a difficult task.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.55,1:31:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, he may have even wondered
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.18,1:31:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,if he was doing the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.97,1:31:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s possible Jehovah provided Josiah
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.89,1:31:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,with assurance from the prophet Jeremiah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.94,1:31:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what Jehovah says: “Look!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.44,1:31:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“A son named Josiah
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.32,1:31:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“will be born to the house of David!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.74,1:31:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“He will sacrifice on you
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.57,1:31:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“the priests of the high places,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.66,1:31:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“those making sacrificial smoke on you,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.08,1:31:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will burn human bones on you.”
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.37,1:32:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That prophecy
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.21,1:32:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,made over 300 years earlier confirmed
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.51,1:32:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that Josiah was the one\Nprophesied to act against false worship.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.51,1:32:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This may have given Josiah\Neven greater incentive and courage
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.68,1:32:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue his campaign,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.85,1:32:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,which now included repairing the temple.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.39,1:32:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,These actions contributed
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.69,1:32:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to the peaceful conditions
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.81,1:32:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that elevated pure worship.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.69,1:32:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Josiah did so much
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.53,1:32:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to restore pure worship.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.91,1:32:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why we love him.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.78,1:32:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, the peoples’ heart condition\Nremained polluted,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.66,1:32:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,so the nation required severe discipline.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.71,1:32:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah prophesied
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.21,1:32:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a conquest of the Babylonians
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.75,1:32:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,against Judah.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.79,1:32:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All this land
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.84,1:32:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,will be reduced to ruins,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.59,1:32:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and this land and its inhabitants
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.42,1:32:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,will have to serve the king of Babylon
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.59,1:32:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,for 70 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.60,1:32:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel himself may have heard
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.64,1:32:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah speak those words.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.27,1:32:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And he certainly
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.64,1:33:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,saw it come true as he and his family\Nwere exiled to Babylon.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.19,1:33:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk about peace being interrupted!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.48,1:33:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel was a young Judean prince taken
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.19,1:33:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,from his homeland
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.20,1:33:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and separated from his family.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.95,1:33:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But being chosen to receive special training
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.20,1:33:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in the court of King Nebuchadnezzar
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.66,1:33:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,presented another set of challenges.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.17,1:33:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire way
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.17,1:33:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of Babylonian life was contrary\Nto what Daniel knew growing up in Judah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.47,1:33:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But Daniel was determined\Nnot to pollute himself
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.55,1:33:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,with foods Jehovah would not approve of.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.89,1:33:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah blessed
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.89,1:33:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel’s determination to be faithful,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.35,1:33:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,as he was selected to serve
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.15,1:33:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as one of King Nebuchadnezzar’s wise men.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.78,1:33:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Nebuchadnezzar was a warrior-king
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.28,1:33:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,intent on building a great empire.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.33,1:34:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,After he officially
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.08,1:34:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,took the throne\Nin 624 B.C.E., his domain
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.58,1:34:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,grew with each conquest.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.63,1:34:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Babylon became an epicenter\Nof trade and commerce.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.09,1:34:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Nebuchadnezzar undertook
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.09,1:34:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,huge building projects throughout the city,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.10,1:34:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which made the city seem impregnable.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.22,1:34:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine the sense of security\Nthe inhabitants of Babylon must have felt,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.69,1:34:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,locked safely behind the city’s walls.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.73,1:34:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Nebuchadnezzar
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.57,1:34:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,attributed the prosperity
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.82,1:34:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and security all around him
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.57,1:34:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to the power of his false gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.78,1:34:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The chief of these false gods\Nwas Marduk, the god of war.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.21,1:34:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, these false gods and their priests\Nwould prove to be worthless.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.42,1:34:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,One night,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.46,1:34:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,King Nebuchadnezzar had a strange dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.43,1:35:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the wise men!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.31,1:35:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,O king, may you live on forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.60,1:35:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Relate the dream to your servants.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.98,1:35:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We will tell the interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.52,1:35:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.90,1:35:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don’t make the dream known to me
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.53,1:35:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,along with the interpretation,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.53,1:35:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll be dismembered,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.16,1:35:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and your houses will be turned into public latrines.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.45,1:35:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There is not a man on earth
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.08,1:35:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,who can do what the king demands.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.54,1:35:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What the king is asking is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.21,1:35:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No one exists
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.42,1:35:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,who could tell this to the king except
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.84,1:35:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,—except the gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.51,1:35:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Seize them!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.43,1:35:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill them!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.43,1:35:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.43,1:35:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re in danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.52,1:35:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? What happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.39,1:35:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t hear everything,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.23,1:35:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but the wise men angered the king.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.98,1:35:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is to be executed by dawn.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.32,1:35:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah here.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.44,1:35:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll try to learn more.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.49,1:35:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This edict to kill all the wise men
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.03,1:36:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,would also include Daniel and his companions.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.16,1:36:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s look at this\Nfrom Daniel’s perspective.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.87,1:36:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Here he is, a young man in a foreign land,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.21,1:36:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,serving in the court of one\Nof the most powerful and violent men alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.88,1:36:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And that man is now demanding
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.21,1:36:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that someone, in effect, read his mind:
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.13,1:36:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“Tell me my dream,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.18,1:36:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell me what it means.”
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.18,1:36:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,O king,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.98,1:36:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,interpretations belong to my God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.69,1:36:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows your dream and what it means.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.73,1:36:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, where is your God?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.32,1:36:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.78,1:36:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe that he—\NI know that he will reveal it to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.91,1:36:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, give me time.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.92,1:36:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel is not acting
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.79,1:36:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,on previous experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.96,1:36:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He hasn’t received interpretations\Nof dreams from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.84,1:36:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, he is acting on faith
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.34,1:37:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,—faith that he had learned
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.22,1:37:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,by studying the sacred books of his time.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.64,1:37:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,These books
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.27,1:37:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,likely included the inspired writings
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.60,1:37:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of Moses, David, Solomon, Isaiah,\NJeremiah, and other prophets.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.57,1:37:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we can only imagine
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.69,1:37:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel poring over these scrolls,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.45,1:37:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,opening up his heart to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.61,1:37:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,begging Jehovah to give him wisdom and understanding.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.08,1:37:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He loved it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.79,1:37:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no doubt that
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.58,1:37:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as Daniel studied these accounts,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.75,1:37:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,his faith was strengthened
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.17,1:37:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and his bond with Jehovah drew even closer.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.67,1:37:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So even though Daniel knew nothing\Nof King Nebuchadnezzar’s dream,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.59,1:37:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,he was fully convinced
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.89,1:37:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah would reveal the dream
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.05,1:37:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and its interpretation
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.14,1:37:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and prove to be Daniel’s salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.02,1:37:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we know exactly which accounts
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.77,1:37:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel was able to draw from at this time?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.65,1:37:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s impossible to say for a certainty,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.32,1:37:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but we do know he had access to “the books.”
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.49,1:38:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He references the prophecies of Jeremiah.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.37,1:38:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel could see how Jehovah blessed\Nfaithful, obedient men in the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.95,1:38:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So by asking Nebuchadnezzar for time,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.71,1:38:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,he wasn’t looking to buy himself
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.62,1:38:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,another day of life;
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.17,1:38:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,he was allowing Jehovah to reward his faith
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.75,1:38:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,by revealing the dream to him.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.68,1:38:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel strikes a balance here.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.76,1:38:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Although he is confident
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.76,1:38:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah will reveal the dream to him,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.77,1:38:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,he isn’t casual in the way\Nhe handled the situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.85,1:38:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He did what any God-fearing man
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.90,1:38:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,would do here.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.48,1:38:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He approached Jehovah in prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.53,1:38:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.53,1:38:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,surely you didn’t bring us here just to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.70,1:38:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What will people say?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.45,1:38:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We told them
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.66,1:38:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are the God of the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.79,1:38:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the only God who can reveal secrets.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.25,1:38:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, vindicate yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.34,1:39:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I have found a man from the exiles of Judah
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.38,1:39:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,who can make known
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.88,1:39:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the interpretation to the king.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.76,1:39:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I know who he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.14,1:39:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you really make known to me
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.77,1:39:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the dream that I saw
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.06,1:39:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and its interpretation?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.03,1:40:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a God in the heavens
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.03,1:40:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,who is a Revealer of secrets,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.91,1:40:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has made known to King Nebuchadnezzar
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.50,1:40:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what is to happen
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.96,1:40:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the final part of the days.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.59,1:40:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your dream:
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.47,1:40:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw an immense image.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.07,1:40:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That image
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.61,1:40:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,was standing in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.36,1:40:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You yourself are the head of gold.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.08,1:40:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But after you another kingdom will rise,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.08,1:40:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,inferior to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.37,1:41:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then another kingdom, a third one, of copper,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.13,1:41:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that will rule over the whole earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.26,1:41:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,As for the fourth kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.63,1:41:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it will be strong like iron.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.93,1:41:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The kingdom will be divided.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.47,1:41:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the toes of the feet
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.60,1:41:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,were partly of iron and partly of clay,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.90,1:41:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so the kingdom will be partly strong
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.40,1:41:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and partly fragile.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.45,1:41:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This took a tremendous amount of faith
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.82,1:41:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and courage on the part of Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.45,1:41:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we may find our peace threatened,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.25,1:41:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,our very lives might be on the line.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.54,1:41:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In that moment, we can turn\Nto Jehovah God in prayer,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.05,1:41:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,opening up our hearts,\Nconfident that he will support us.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.30,1:41:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Like both Daniel and Jonah,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.39,1:41:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve been given an assignment
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.01,1:41:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to proclaim a message.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.02,1:41:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This requires courage to speak out boldly
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.68,1:41:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,concerning Jehovah’s judgments
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.60,1:42:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,against those who oppose his sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.61,1:42:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of these prophets are excellent examples
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.36,1:42:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah backing those who trust in him.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.49,1:42:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will always be with us\Nas long as we have faith in him.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.41,1:42:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When we face situations that seem impossible,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.54,1:42:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as in the case with Hezekiah,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.62,1:42:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the ability to tap
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.75,1:42:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,into the most powerful force there is!
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.84,1:42:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,As this system comes to a close,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.47,1:42:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we will find ourselves in situations
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.22,1:42:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that test our courage and threaten our peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.93,1:42:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We will have to stand up\Nfor pure worship
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.85,1:42:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,just like Josiah, and this will be unpopular.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.56,1:42:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But with Jehovah on our side,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.86,1:42:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we can face those situations with confidence.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.57,1:42:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s all-powerful,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.61,1:42:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s going to help us through it.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.24,1:42:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here’s the interesting thing:
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.28,1:42:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the prophecies that Daniel recorded
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.66,1:42:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,applied not only to the future\Nof the Babylonian Empire
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.21,1:43:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but also outline world events
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.63,1:43:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to our day and beyond.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.71,1:43:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And these events are being fulfilled
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.59,1:43:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,right before our very eyes!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.60,1:43:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What a motivating presentation!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.40,1:43:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when our peace is threatened,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.90,1:43:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we can focus on how our integrity\Nrelates to Jehovah’s purpose,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.91,1:43:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can endure with joy.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.12,1:43:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We look forward to watching Part 2\Nof this important consideration
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.37,1:43:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,during the final session of our convention.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.75,1:43:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s sing together song number 130,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.88,1:43:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,entitled “Be Forgiving.”
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.84,1:43:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s song number 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.42,0:00:26.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんを温かく歓迎いたします
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.13,0:00:31.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,これから2日目午後のプログラムを\Nご一緒に楽しみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.72,0:00:34.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,人と平和な関係を築くために
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.43,0:00:37.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,一人一人に何ができるかを学びます
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.77,0:00:42.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,では最初に\Nミュージックビデオを見ましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.19,0:00:45.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界的な家族に人々を迎え入れて
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.48,0:00:48.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を楽しんでもらいたいと\N感じるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.69,0:00:50.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.55,0:10:15.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,では ご一緒に29番の歌
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.60,0:10:19.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバの証人として生きる」を\N歌いましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.31,0:10:22.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌は29番です
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.63,0:12:55.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の不完全さによって 自分の平和や
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.09,0:12:58.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,人の平和が乱されることがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.51,0:13:00.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のシンポジウムで
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.55,0:13:04.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和な関係を築くために\N避けなければならないことを
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.81,0:13:07.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,5つ考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.89,0:13:11.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではまず出版委員会の援助者
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.52,0:13:14.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハロルド･コーカーン兄弟の話に
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.07,0:13:16.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,耳を傾けましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.28,0:13:19.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,「平和を壊すものを『脱ぎ捨てる』
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.07,0:13:21.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,自慢」という主題です
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.89,0:13:31.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,このシンポジウムのキーワードは
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.31,0:13:33.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,「脱ぎ捨てる」です
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.98,0:13:36.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,関連する表現としてほかにも
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.36,0:13:40.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,「捨て去る」とか「取り除く」とか
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.70,0:13:44.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,「取り去る」というものがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.99,0:13:49.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,クリスチャンは何を\N「脱ぎ捨てる」必要がありますか
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.08,0:13:51.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,その答えは 聖書の
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.58,0:13:54.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,エフェソス 4:22に書かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.96,0:13:58.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,エフェソス 4:22です
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.88,0:14:03.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,「皆さんは 古い人格を\N脱ぎ捨てるようにと教えられました
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.76,0:14:07.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人格は\N以前の生き方に基づくもので
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.73,0:14:11.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪い欲望に引きずられて\N腐敗していきます」
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.73,0:14:15.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは「古い人格を脱ぎ捨て」ました
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.73,0:14:17.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 脱ぎ捨てるだけでなく
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.94,0:14:21.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,また身に着けないように\Nしなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.45,0:14:27.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでパウロは 次の節\N23節でこう勧めています
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.29,0:14:33.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,「考え方を新しくする\N努力を続けましょう」
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.71,0:14:37.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,古い人格は平和を壊してしまうので
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.38,0:14:40.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,再び身に着けないようにすることが
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.26,0:14:42.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても重要です
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.76,0:14:47.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,このシンポジウムでは5つ
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.22,0:14:50.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を壊す事柄を取り上げます
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.90,0:14:55.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,それぞれの話で取り上げられる\N平和を壊すものが
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.15,0:14:58.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず どんなものかを学びます
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.69,0:15:02.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,2つ目に\Nそれがどのように平和を壊すか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.62,0:15:07.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,3つ目に それをどのように\N脱ぎ捨てるかを考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.16,0:15:11.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず最初に取り上げるのは何でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.79,0:15:16.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは 自慢することです
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.30,0:15:18.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,自慢とは何でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.05,0:15:21.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分を称賛することです
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.63,0:15:25.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことについて 格言 27:2には
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.64,0:15:30.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,「自分の口ではなく\N別の人があなたを称賛するようにせよ
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.19,0:15:36.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の唇ではなくほかの人たちが」と\N書かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.03,0:15:40.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分を称賛することは誇りの表れで
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.03,0:15:45.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分をほかの人よりも\N高めていることになります
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.49,0:15:48.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教で得られた成果を含め
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.37,0:15:51.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の成し遂げたことを\N誇る人もいます
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.04,0:15:54.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,1世紀にはどんなことが\Nあったでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.92,0:15:59.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは コリントの会衆の\N兄弟姉妹の間で不和が生じ
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.67,0:16:02.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和が損なわれていることを\N指摘しました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.97,0:16:07.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の中に「思い上がって」いる\N人たちがいたからです
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.14,0:16:10.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分はパウロに従う アポロに従う
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.31,0:16:13.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,ケファに従う という人たちもいました
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.06,0:16:19.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分や他の人に\N過度の注意を向けていたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.49,0:16:22.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,今も同じようなことが生じ得ます
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.78,0:16:26.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹がおしゃべりをしている時に\N1人がこう言います
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.87,0:16:29.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,「よく祈って頑張ったら
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.20,0:16:33.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのおかげで\N聖書レッスンが見つかったんです」
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.92,0:16:37.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,するとすかさず 別の人がこう言います
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.67,0:16:41.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は4人と勉強していて\N2人は集会に来ていて
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.55,0:16:44.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,1人はもうすぐバプテスマなんです」
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.14,0:16:48.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和が壊れてしまうのでは\Nないでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.27,0:16:54.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,確かに 自慢すると\N平和が壊れてしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.31,0:16:59.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,宣教を楽しむのも 良い成果が\N得られた時にエホバに感謝するのも
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.28,0:17:01.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いことではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.53,0:17:04.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 自分の成し遂げたことを\N自慢すると
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.07,0:17:09.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,競争心やねたみや対抗心を\Nあおってしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.04,0:17:12.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分をアピールすることは
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.54,0:17:15.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,「平和の神」エホバからの\Nものではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.59,0:17:17.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,どこから出るものでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.00,0:17:21.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨハネ第一 2:16にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.51,0:17:25.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,「持ち物を見せびらかすことは皆\N父からのものではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.60,0:17:28.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,世から出るものだからです」
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.68,0:17:33.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,世の中には 自分をアピールする人が\N大勢いるのではないでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.77,0:17:37.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,SNSでもそういう人を見掛けます
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.11,0:17:39.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分に注目してもらうために
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.23,0:17:43.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,いろいろな写真や動画をアップします
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.07,0:17:47.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の成し遂げたことや持ち物や
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.24,0:17:50.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,ぜいたくな旅行の様子を投稿し
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.37,0:17:52.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,見せびらかします
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.87,0:17:57.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私を見て いいでしょ？」と\Nいうわけです
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.42,0:18:02.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分をアピールすることは\N平和を壊す 世の精神です
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.26,0:18:05.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういう精神に\N染まらないようにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.35,0:18:09.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を壊すものである自慢は
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.14,0:18:12.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,どれほど悲惨な結果に\Nつながるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.06,0:18:16.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書に出てくるハマンの例を\N考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.77,0:18:18.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハマンはプライドが高く
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.98,0:18:21.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,高慢で 自慢ばかりしていました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.61,0:18:25.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,エステル 5章によると\Nハマンは家族や友人に
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.32,0:18:29.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の富のこと 多くの息子のこと
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.16,0:18:33.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が自分を他の家来たちより\N高い地位に就けたこと
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.92,0:18:38.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,王と王妃に宴会に招かれたことを\N自慢しました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.75,0:18:42.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハマンは傲慢な悪人でした
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.67,0:18:47.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに仕える人モルデカイを\N殺そうとしました
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.93,0:18:52.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,やがて ハマンの正体とたくらみが\N暴露されます
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.02,0:18:56.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,モルデカイを掛けようとして\N用意した杭に
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.15,0:18:58.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分が掛けられたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.98,0:19:01.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,この出来事について考えると
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.44,0:19:05.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,イザヤ 29:20の\N次の言葉を思い出します
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.70,0:19:09.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,「自慢する者は終わりを迎え［る］」
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.58,0:19:15.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,自慢することが 自分や他の人に\Nどれほど悪い影響を与えるかを考えると
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.33,0:19:20.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは 自慢しているという\N印象さえ与えたくありません
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.59,0:19:23.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のビデオをご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.30,0:19:25.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある姉妹の言動が
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.76,0:19:29.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,自慢と受け止められてしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.81,0:19:38.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あらゆる悪意 怒り 憤り わめき
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.69,0:19:44.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,暴言など 一切の有害な事柄を\N捨て去ってください」
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.95,0:19:47.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,朝起きて 「今日はあの兄弟に
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.53,0:19:52.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪意のある言葉を言ってやろう」と\N思った人がいますか
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.12,0:19:57.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,いないでしょう でも\N意図せずそうなることはありますね
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:20:02.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を壊さない鍵は 心からの愛です
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.09,0:20:07.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹のことをよく知れば\N愛は強くなります
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.85,0:20:13.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄弟姉妹が経験している喜びや痛み
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.23,0:20:16.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,熱い思い
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.65,0:20:21.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに引き寄せられたこと
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.15,0:20:25.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,耐えていることなどをよく考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.49,0:20:34.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かった すぐ帰る じゃあね\Nああ 大変
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.04,0:20:38.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリー！
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.38,0:20:39.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,あっ 行かなきゃいけなくて
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.92,0:20:41.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,オッケー 後で電話する
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.55,0:20:43.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがと またね\Nまたね またね
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.97,0:20:46.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,午後の方が良さそう
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.14,0:20:50.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,おばあちゃん！\Nあらまあヘイリー
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.26,0:20:52.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほんとにごめんなさいね
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.89,0:20:55.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,全然大丈夫
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.98,0:20:59.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,片付けるね\Nああ
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.61,0:21:03.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,大丈夫だった？\Nありがとう 悪いね
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.07,0:21:05.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいのよ ちょっと待ってて
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.41,0:21:15.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがとう
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.92,0:21:19.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,おばあちゃん 今日日曜日だから
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.84,0:21:22.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,こっちだね\N今日もいろいろあったもんね
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.71,0:21:25.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほんとにそうね
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.14,0:21:32.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,おやすみなさい
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.68,0:22:14.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんこんにちは\Nデミュアデザインのヘイリーです
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.43,0:22:17.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,さりげないおしゃれを日常に
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.27,0:22:22.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めての方も いつも見てくれている\N方も 見てくれてありがとうございます
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.23,0:22:27.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,初めに紹介するのは このかわいい\Nピアスとネックレスのセットです
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.45,0:22:32.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,淡い色で作ってみたので どんな色の\Nお洋服にも似合うと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.54,0:22:34.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっとこれ見てよ
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.45,0:22:35.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,形もかわいいし\N質感もとてもいいですよ
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.00,0:22:37.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,仕事でやってるやつでしょ
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.96,0:22:40.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,セットで着けると\Nとってもおしゃれです
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.92,0:22:44.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,主張し過ぎないけど\N大人っぽさをプラス！
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.51,0:22:48.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,まだの方は チャンネル登録も\Nよろしくお願いします
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.39,0:22:53.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,着けるとこんな感じ すてきでしょ？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.19,0:23:03.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ビデオの姉妹は\Nあからさまに自慢していたでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.69,0:23:07.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ 姉妹はエホバに仕える\N謙遜な人です
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.74,0:23:11.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,祖母を優しく世話することもしています
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.91,0:23:16.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 仕事で作っている\Nアクセサリーを紹介する動画で
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.46,0:23:20.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,何と言っていましたか\Nこう言っていました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.29,0:23:24.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,「着けるとこんな感じ\Nすてきでしょ？」
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.30,0:23:29.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,動画を見たある姉妹は心を乱され
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.01,0:23:34.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,その姉妹が自慢していると感じました
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.56,0:23:36.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の言葉や行動が
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.81,0:23:41.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,人にどう受け止められるかを\N考えることは大切です
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.77,0:23:48.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 自慢という平和を壊すものを\Nどのように脱ぎ捨てられるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.40,0:23:51.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,心に留めておくべき大切な点が
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.78,0:23:56.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,コリント第一 4:7に書かれています
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.25,0:24:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,コリント第一 4:7です
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.04,0:24:02.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.09,0:24:05.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたの何が他の人より\N優れているのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.59,0:24:09.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが持っているもので\Nもらったのではないものがあるのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.93,0:24:11.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,もらったのであれば
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.97,0:24:15.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしてもらったのではないかのように\N誇るのですか」
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.02,0:24:18.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ポイントは何でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.60,0:24:20.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,自慢するのではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.81,0:24:26.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の成し遂げたことは\N全てエホバのおかげだと認めることです
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.40,0:24:28.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々はいろいろなことを誇ります
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.78,0:24:33.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,外見や 人気や 富や 地位や
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.20,0:24:37.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,身体能力や 音楽の才能などです
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.00,0:24:40.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,古代イスラエルのダビデ王は
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.42,0:24:43.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,その全てを持っていました
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.38,0:24:48.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもダビデは 自慢することは\Nありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.13,0:24:51.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつも謙遜でした なぜでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.18,0:24:54.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,詩編 113:5-8で
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.81,0:24:58.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデはエホバに注意を向けています
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.18,0:25:03.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,「立場が低い」自分のために\N身をかがめ 地面から引き上げて
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.11,0:25:07.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,「高貴な人たちと共に座」らせて\Nくださったと言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.36,0:25:10.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,またダビデは いろいろな機会に
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.32,0:25:12.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバを賛美せよ」とか
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.03,0:25:16.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神の聖なる名を誇れ」と言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.45,0:25:20.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちもエホバを誇りとすべきです
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.00,0:25:25.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロも コリント第一 1:31で\Nこう勧めています
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.84,0:25:29.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,「誇る人はエホバについて\N誇るべきです」
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.51,0:25:31.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,どういう意味でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.76,0:25:36.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,真の神を知っていること\Nエホバの望むことを行うため
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.72,0:25:40.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに使っていただけることを\N誇るのです
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.02,0:25:46.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,自慢しないためにできることが\Nほかにもあります
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.82,0:25:49.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分のことばかり話すのではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.78,0:25:52.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,仲間の良いところや
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.07,0:25:55.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い行いについて話すことです
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.49,0:25:58.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,謙遜で慎み深い人は
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.75,0:26:01.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分のしたことについて\N誇ったりしません
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.92,0:26:04.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,むしろエホバが兄弟姉妹を\Nどのように用い
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.00,0:26:07.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,祝福しているかに注意を向けます
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.67,0:26:11.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば 雰囲気はとても和やかで
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.09,0:26:13.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和なものになるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.39,0:26:18.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでは 自慢という\N平和を壊すものを脱ぎ捨て
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.56,0:26:20.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,また身に着けないようにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.89,0:26:24.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのために 何を成し遂げるとしても
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.40,0:26:27.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを賛美したいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.19,0:26:30.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 仲間の良いところを褒め
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.07,0:26:34.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが仲間をどう用いているかに\N注意を向けましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.33,0:26:38.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば 貴重な平和を\N守ることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.54,0:26:42.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとも 兄弟姉妹ともです
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.46,0:26:47.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕委員会の援助者\Nセス･ハイアット兄弟が
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.88,0:26:50.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,シンポジウムの次の話をします
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.22,0:26:55.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題は「平和を壊すものを\N『脱ぎ捨てる』 ねたみ」です
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.81,0:27:06.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみとは何でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.19,0:27:10.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみがどんなふうに表れるかを\N知っておくことは大切です
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.78,0:27:12.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.99,0:27:16.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみは憎しみの一種だからです
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.91,0:27:19.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を壊すものです
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.50,0:27:21.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,注意していないと
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.75,0:27:25.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの関係も壊れてしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.00,0:27:30.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書によれば ねたみには\N2つの症状があるといえます
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.59,0:27:33.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つ目はすぐ思い付く症状です
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.80,0:27:38.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは 人が持っているものを\N欲しがることです
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.39,0:27:44.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもねたみには もう一つの\N症状があるので 非常に厄介です
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.98,0:27:49.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,その症状とは 人の持っているものを\N欲しがるだけでなく
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.99,0:27:54.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,それをその人に持って\Nほしくないと思うことです
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.28,0:27:56.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,例を考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.70,0:28:00.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,1世紀にユダヤ人の宗教指導者たちは
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.96,0:28:06.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスをねたみました\Nイエスが人々に好かれていたからです
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.50,0:28:09.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスは立場の低い人たちを含め
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.51,0:28:12.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々に敬意を持って接していました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.34,0:28:16.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 多くの人に愛されました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.22,0:28:19.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,宗教指導者たちはねたみました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.10,0:28:24.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,人々に対する自分たちの\N接し方を変えるのではなく
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.40,0:28:27.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスのことを悪く言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.73,0:28:31.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの評判を落とそうとしたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.07,0:28:34.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,中傷し 悪いうわさを広めました
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.53,0:28:38.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまり イエスが持っていたものを\N欲しがっただけでなく 
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.33,0:28:41.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,それをイエスに持たせたく\Nなかったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.50,0:28:45.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみは ガラテア 5:21で
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.08,0:28:49.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,「罪深い欲望から出る行い」の\N1つに挙げられています
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.01,0:28:52.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみはとても危険なので
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.63,0:28:55.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,何としても避けたいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.72,0:29:01.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみはどのように\N平和を壊すのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.85,0:29:08.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみは家族や会衆の絆を弱め
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.57,0:29:14.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,やがてその絆を破壊してしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.07,0:29:21.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブと12人の息子の事を\N考えてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.54,0:29:27.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブは息子のヨセフを\N特別に愛していました
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.42,0:29:30.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで兄たちはねたむようになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.88,0:29:35.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らのねたみはどのような形で\N表れたでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.43,0:29:41.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,兄たちはヨセフにつらく当たり\N奴隷として売ってしまいました
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.14,0:29:45.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,それだけでなく\Nヤコブにうそをつきました
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.23,0:29:47.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ヨセフは死んでしまった」
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.94,0:29:50.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう報告したのです
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.32,0:29:53.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族が慰めようとしても
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.99,0:29:57.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブは聞こうとしませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.57,0:30:01.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨセフの死を何年も悲しみました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.28,0:30:05.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみは悲惨な結果につながりました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.21,0:30:07.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうした結果から分かる通り
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.58,0:30:10.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみの気持ちを抱いていると
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.21,0:30:15.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛や親切や思いやりが\N影を潜めてしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.88,0:30:20.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,その代わりに 憎しみや敵意や
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.30,0:30:24.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りなどを表すようになってしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.27,0:30:29.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 会衆への影響についても\N考えてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.48,0:30:33.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,コラ ダタン アビラムの事を\N思い出してください
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.90,0:30:40.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼らはイスラエルの民の中での\Nモーセとアロンの立場をねたみました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.37,0:30:44.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみはどんな形で表れたでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.87,0:30:50.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバから任命された2人について\N批判的なことを言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.25,0:30:53.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,モーセを非難し 「エホバの会衆に
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.09,0:30:57.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,君臨しようとしている」\Nとまで言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.67,0:31:00.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,モーセとアロンに責任を委ねたのが
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.93,0:31:05.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバである という事実を\N見失っていたことが分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.35,0:31:09.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを見ていたエホバは
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.35,0:31:12.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,どう行動したでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.48,0:31:17.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,3人とその反逆に加わった人たちを\N滅ぼしました
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.07,0:31:21.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時のイスラエルの会衆の\N平和が失われてしまったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.74,0:31:27.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうした記述から エホバがねたみを\Nどう見ているかが分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.00,0:31:31.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも こう思うかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.08,0:31:33.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は相手を傷つけてまで
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.34,0:31:37.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人の持っているものを\N奪おうなんて思わない」
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.84,0:31:39.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 私たちは不完全です
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.01,0:31:45.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,心は信用できないので\N気付かないうちにねたむことがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.31,0:31:47.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ドラマの続きを見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.85,0:31:53.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみによって 平和が\Nどのように脅かされるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.13,0:32:16.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,また？\Nどうしたの？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.01,0:32:21.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,あ ヘイリー かわいいじゃない
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.18,0:32:23.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうだ ネックレス\N買おうと思ってたんだった
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.43,0:32:26.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,え 姉妹も？やり過ぎだと思いません？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.89,0:32:28.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなことないわよ
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.47,0:32:30.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなヘイリーの話ばっかり
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.85,0:32:34.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリーもまんざらでもなさそう
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.73,0:32:38.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリーが悪いってこと？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.78,0:32:42.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はそう思ったんですけど
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.07,0:32:46.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,お茶が冷めちゃう
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.62,0:32:51.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,話そらすんですね
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.29,0:32:53.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうじゃないけど
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.58,0:32:56.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,前もその話 してたよね
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.92,0:32:59.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしたの？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.38,0:33:03.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリーは一緒に開拓してる友達でしょ
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.47,0:33:06.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,だから心配してるんです
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.51,0:33:10.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,心配してあげるのはいいことだけど
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.56,0:33:16.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっとねたんでるところない？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.37,0:33:29.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,エミリーはどんな様子でしたか
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.79,0:33:34.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみの気持ちが\N心に芽生えていましたね
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.21,0:33:39.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリーの動機を疑っているようでした
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.13,0:33:46.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリーの評判を下げてしまうような\Nことを言っていました
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.47,0:33:50.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,こういうことは誰にでも起きます
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.93,0:33:53.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみの気持ちに\N負けないようにするには
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.64,0:33:56.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしたらよいでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.48,0:33:59.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちにできる2つのことがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.02,0:34:04.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,謙遜になることと 満足することです
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.49,0:34:10.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず 聖書が謙遜さについて\N何と述べているか見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.37,0:34:12.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,フィリピ 2章をご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.83,0:34:15.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,3節から読みます
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.04,0:34:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,フィリピ 2:3
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.59,0:34:28.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,「対抗心を抱いたり 自己中心的に\Nなったりしてはなりません」
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.18,0:34:30.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,自己中心的な人は
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.35,0:34:35.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分のことを実際以上に\N優れていると考えがちです
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.02,0:34:39.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの時代の宗教指導者たちや
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.15,0:34:42.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨセフの兄たちや
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.73,0:34:46.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,コラ ダタン アビラムは
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.86,0:34:49.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,まさにそういう人たちでした
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.32,0:34:51.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう思いませんか
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.58,0:34:54.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 他人事ではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.25,0:34:57.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰にでもそうなってしまう\N危険があります
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.62,0:35:00.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしたらいいでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.50,0:35:03.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖句の続きを見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.38,0:35:08.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,「謙遜になり 自分より他の人の方が\N上だと考えてください」
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.26,0:35:14.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまり 自分より他の人の方が\N重要だと考えるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.10,0:35:17.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう考える人は
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.35,0:35:19.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のアドバイスに従います
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.65,0:35:21.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,4節です
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.06,0:35:25.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,「自分のことばかり考えずに
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.82,0:35:29.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の人のことにも気を配りましょう」
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.99,0:35:35.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,謙遜であれば 人のことに気を配ります
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.62,0:35:40.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の方が人より重要だとは考えません
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.29,0:35:43.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,満足することも大切です
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.54,0:35:45.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,持っているもので満足します
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.67,0:35:48.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,奉仕の立場や割り当て
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.92,0:35:51.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,持っているものについて
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.34,0:35:54.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分をほかの人と比較しません
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.76,0:35:57.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,満足しているからです
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.35,0:36:01.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,謙遜であり 満足するなら
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.15,0:36:03.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,人をねたむことはないでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.52,0:36:06.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに助けてもらいながら
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.53,0:36:11.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねたみという平和を壊すものを\N脱ぎ捨てましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.28,0:36:15.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうするなら 自分自身\N穏やかな気持ちになり
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.53,0:36:20.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,家庭にも会衆にも\N平和をつくることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.75,0:36:25.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは心から喜んでくださるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.17,0:36:30.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,出版委員会の援助者\Nガイユス･グロッケンティン兄弟が
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.47,0:36:33.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,シンポジウムの次の話を\Nしてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.72,0:36:38.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題は「平和を壊すものを\N『脱ぎ捨てる』 不正直」
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.23,0:36:49.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,不正直と聞くと誰を思い出しますか
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.28,0:36:53.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,「うその根源」と呼ばれている\Nサタンでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.03,0:36:56.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるいは アナニアと\N妻のサッピラですか
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.91,0:37:01.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人はうそをついたために\N命を失いました
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.12,0:37:03.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンやこの2人のような
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.50,0:37:06.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,うそつきにはなりたくありません
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.79,0:37:11.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,では あからさまなうそをつかなければ\Nそれでいいのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.88,0:37:18.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖なる神エホバはご自分の民に\N聖なる人であってほしいと願っています
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.77,0:37:22.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 人を「だましてはなら」ないと\N命じています
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.52,0:37:26.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,レビ記 19:11にある通りです
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.19,0:37:31.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここから正直さについて何が学べますか
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.49,0:37:35.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,正直さには人をだまさないこと
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.66,0:37:39.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまり相手に間違った印象を\N与えるようなことを
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.24,0:37:42.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,意図的に言わないことが含まれます
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.62,0:37:45.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 事実をゆがめたり
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.79,0:37:48.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,都合のいいことだけを言ったりするなら
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.42,0:37:51.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の人との平和が損なわれます
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.38,0:37:53.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜそう言えますか
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.42,0:37:58.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,不正直によって どのように\N平和は壊れてしまうでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.10,0:38:04.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和や良い関係は\N信頼の上に築かれます
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.69,0:38:07.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,信頼できる人と一緒にいると
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.56,0:38:11.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,心地よく 安心できます
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.69,0:38:15.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,信頼のないところに平和はありません
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.28,0:38:18.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,信頼はどのように築かれますか
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.20,0:38:24.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,一緒に過ごし 互いに真実を\N語ることによって築かれます
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.00,0:38:29.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが信頼するのは\N聖書が言う「不正直な話し方」
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.21,0:38:32.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,「曲がった話し方」をしない人です
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.71,0:38:35.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰かが一度でも不正直な話し方をすると
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.84,0:38:41.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人の話は全て信じられなく\Nなってしまうかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.39,0:38:45.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,たった一度不正直な話し方をしただけで
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.23,0:38:48.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,評判が傷ついてしまうのです
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.40,0:38:51.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,それだけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.44,0:38:56.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,場合によっては\Nもっと深刻な問題につながります
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.53,0:39:01.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,不正直は 感染力の強い\Nウイルスのようです
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.54,0:39:07.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,不正直というウイルスは\N他の人にうつります
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.50,0:39:09.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,不正直な人に接していると
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.58,0:39:14.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分もそのウイルスに\N感染してしまうかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.88,0:39:19.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,その被害は 相手との\N人間関係だけにとどまりません
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.43,0:39:21.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,連鎖的に広まって
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.47,0:39:26.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,みんなの平和と一致が\N損なわれてしまうことがあるのです
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.52,0:39:29.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の創世記に出てくる
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.73,0:39:34.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラバンとヤコブとの間で起きた\N出来事を思い出します
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.78,0:39:37.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブはラバンとの約束に基づいて
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.65,0:39:40.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,7年間一生懸命働きました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.70,0:39:43.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,娘のラケルと結婚するためです
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.95,0:39:48.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブは7年という\N長い期間にわたって働きましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.87,0:39:51.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラケルを深く愛していたので
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.67,0:39:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ほんの数日」のように思いました
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.46,0:40:01.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,ところが 妻として与えられたのは\Nラケルではなく 姉のレアでした
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.59,0:40:06.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから レアもヤコブを\Nだましていたことになります
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.48,0:40:12.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラバンにだまされたことを知った\Nヤコブはどう思ったでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.52,0:40:17.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,裏切られたと感じ ラバンのことを\N信用できなくなったでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.07,0:40:22.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,不正直によって人間関係や\N平和が壊れてしまったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.74,0:40:28.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかもその後 ラケルのために\Nもう7年働かなければなりませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.46,0:40:33.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラバンの不正直なやり方は\Nその後もまだまだ続きます
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.08,0:40:37.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,不当にも ヤコブの報酬を\N10回も変えました
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.34,0:40:40.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブをだましたのです
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.43,0:40:46.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラバンが不正直だったため\N家族全体の平和が壊れてしまいました
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.48,0:40:53.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではこれから ドラマの続く部分を\N見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.44,0:40:56.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,エミリーとセリアはカフェにいました
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.65,0:41:01.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,エミリーがどのように\N真実をゆがめているか
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.40,0:41:04.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,注意深くご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.32,0:41:07.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリーは一緒に開拓してる友達でしょ
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.33,0:41:09.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,だから心配してるんです
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.62,0:41:13.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,心配してあげるのはいいことだけど
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.54,0:41:17.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっとねたんでるところない？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.09,0:41:22.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かってくれると思ってたのに
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.80,0:41:25.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが感じていることは分かるわよ
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.43,0:41:27.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもヘイリーのことは？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.43,0:41:30.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,全部を見たわけじゃないけど
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.60,0:41:33.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,何か不道徳な投稿があったの？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.94,0:41:35.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ないですけど
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.86,0:41:39.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,良かった そんなはずないよね
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.23,0:41:44.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも もし限度を\N超えているっていうことなら
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.74,0:41:46.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,話は別だけどね
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.03,0:41:49.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリーと話してみたら？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.17,0:41:55.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうですね
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.00,0:42:01.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,エミリー あなたはよく頑張っていて\Nとてもすてきな姉妹よ
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.76,0:42:05.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,あのね
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.47,0:42:09.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,私も長いこと
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.47,0:42:15.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,人と比べてしまう\N傾向があったんだけどね
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.90,0:42:20.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのせいで自分も傷ついたし
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.19,0:42:23.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,友達も傷つけちゃったの
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.75,0:42:36.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,セリア姉妹に話さなければ\Nよかったってこと？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.00,0:42:40.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,いや 話してよかったと思うよ
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.21,0:42:43.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,信頼できる姉妹だしね
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.47,0:42:45.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹は何て？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.43,0:42:48.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,「すごくよく分かる」って言ってくれた
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.43,0:42:50.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,良かったね
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.68,0:42:54.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリーの動画のことは？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.81,0:42:58.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,うーん\N「全部は見てない」って言ってたけど
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.77,0:43:00.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,うーん
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.36,0:43:03.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,「限度を超えてるから
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.57,0:43:07.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリーは もっと\N気を付けなきゃいけない」って
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.41,0:43:09.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹も言ってた
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.95,0:43:15.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,何かアドバイスくれた？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.79,0:43:20.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,「やめるように言った方がいい」って\N言われた
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.38,0:43:23.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもそんなの無理！
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.59,0:43:27.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねえ
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.22,0:43:33.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,セリア姉妹がそんなふうに\N言ってるんだったら
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.22,0:43:37.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリーと話した方がいいよ
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.56,0:43:43.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっと話すタイミングがあるよ
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.20,0:43:53.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かってくれてありがとう
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.08,0:43:57.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,おなかすいた 祈ってくれる？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.21,0:43:59.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,よし
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.75,0:44:06.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ 親切に今日の夕飯を\N与えてくださり 感謝します ・・・
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.76,0:44:16.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,エミリーは自分の都合のいいように\N話を聞いていましたね
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.64,0:44:21.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,夫のジェイクに話す時には\Nいくらか脚色していました
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.11,0:44:24.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,セリアは実際には\Nヘイリーの投稿について
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.15,0:44:26.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいとも悪いとも言っていませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.90,0:44:31.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,また 「ヘイリーに投稿をやめるように\N言ったら」とも言いませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.28,0:44:34.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,必要なら話し合うよう勧めただけです
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.91,0:44:38.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,仲間には真実を語るべきです
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.12,0:44:43.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもエミリーは事実をゆがめました\N不正直でした
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.25,0:44:48.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,後で分かりますが\N大きな問題に発展します
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.67,0:44:54.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは 不正直という平和を壊すもの\Nを脱ぎ捨てるようにと言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.22,0:44:57.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちがいつでも正直であることを\N望んでいます
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.68,0:44:59.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,小さなことでもです
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.81,0:45:05.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,では どうすれば不正直を\N脱ぎ捨てられますか
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.65,0:45:09.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず 正直でなければならない\N理由に注目しましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.65,0:45:11.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,エフェソス 4章にある
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.70,0:45:14.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロの言葉を見てみたいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.78,0:45:18.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,エフェソス 4:25です
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.95,0:45:20.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.21,0:45:26.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,「皆さんは偽りを捨て去ったのですから
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.13,0:45:29.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,隣人に真実を語りましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.47,0:45:34.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは皆で1つの体を\N構成しているのです」
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.26,0:45:37.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,偽りを捨て去り 
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.47,0:45:41.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,互いに真実を語るべきなのはなぜですか
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.98,0:45:46.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私たちは皆で1つの体を\N構成している」からです
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.11,0:45:51.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,不正直は 同じ体を構成している\N兄弟姉妹に悪い影響を与えます
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.99,0:45:55.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,信頼関係も損なわれてしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.45,0:45:58.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,不正直を脱ぎ捨てるべき理由が\Nよく分かりました
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.99,0:46:03.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 脱ぎ捨てるには\Nどうしたらいいですか
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.46,0:46:08.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,正直であることと不正直であることの\N結果を考えることです
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.63,0:46:11.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,それが大きな助けになります
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.30,0:46:16.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず 不正直がどんな結果に\Nなるかを考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.14,0:46:19.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラバンとヤコブの例から分かる通り
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.72,0:46:24.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の人との平和な関係が\N壊れてしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.23,0:46:27.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,またエホバは不正直を憎んでいるので
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.27,0:46:31.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの平和な関係も\N壊れてしまいます
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.99,0:46:38.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,逆に 正直であることは\Nどんな結果につながりますか
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.91,0:46:43.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,不正直な言い方をすれば その場を\Nうまく切り抜けられるかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.37,0:46:45.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも長い目で見ると
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.42,0:46:49.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,正直であれば良い友を\N作ることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.46,0:46:52.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和な関係を楽しみたいと\N思っている人は
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.84,0:46:57.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,信頼できる人を友にしたいと\N思っています
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.39,0:47:00.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,信頼関係を築ければ
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.10,0:47:04.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,体の各器官である私たちは一致できます
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.48,0:47:07.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらに大切な点として
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.15,0:47:13.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,晴れ晴れとした良心を持ち\N「神との平和」を楽しむことができます
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.61,0:47:18.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 平和を壊すものである\N不正直を脱ぎ捨てましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.28,0:47:21.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,小さなことでも\N正直であるようにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.58,0:47:23.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,不完全な私たちにとって
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.79,0:47:26.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,これが簡単ではないことを
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.29,0:47:29.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはよくご存じです
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.13,0:47:31.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも私たちを助けてくれます
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.84,0:47:36.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 信頼と平和を築き\N壊さないようにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.22,0:47:41.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすればエホバは 私たちの努力を\N祝福してくださるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.27,0:47:45.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,人事委員会の援助者\Nパトリック･ラフランカ兄弟が
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.85,0:47:48.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,シンポジウムの次の話をします
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.10,0:47:51.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題は「平和を壊すものを\N『脱ぎ捨てる』 
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.48,0:47:54.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いうわさ話」です
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.16,0:48:03.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたはうわさ話をしますか
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.87,0:48:06.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰かについて話をすることは
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.62,0:48:09.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,うわさ話の一種です
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.13,0:48:12.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは人に関心があるので\Nこう言うかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.46,0:48:15.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,「スミス兄弟の体調が心配ですね」
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.92,0:48:20.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ブラウン姉妹が伝道で\N良い経験をしたのを聞いた？」
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.26,0:48:24.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは悪いうわさ話でしょうか\Nそうではないでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.27,0:48:26.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 注意する必要があります
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.60,0:48:28.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,テモテ第一 5:13で
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.90,0:48:32.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロはある姉妹たちが\N「うわさ話をしたり
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.57,0:48:36.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,人のことに干渉したりして」いる\Nと言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.57,0:48:40.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちは人の生活で起きていること\N全てを知る必要も
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.82,0:48:43.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰かに知らせる必要もありません
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.58,0:48:45.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,スミス兄弟は 自分の病気について
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.91,0:48:50.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,詳しいことを人に知られたくない\Nと思っているかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.25,0:48:53.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,プライバシーを尊重したいと思います
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.25,0:48:55.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるいは ブラウン姉妹の経験を聞いて
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.71,0:48:58.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,こう言う人がいたらどうでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.22,0:49:02.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,「姉妹はいつも伝道の成果を\N自慢するんだよね」
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.60,0:49:05.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,うわさ話がネガティブな内容になると
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.85,0:49:08.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,中傷に発展しかねません
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.43,0:49:11.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,中傷とは 人の評判を傷つけるために
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.73,0:49:15.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,事実ではない話をすることです
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.36,0:49:20.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いうわさ話は どのように\N平和を壊すでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.78,0:49:23.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが誰かについて悪いうわさ話をし
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.74,0:49:26.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,それが相手の耳に入ったとしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.45,0:49:29.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人は次に会う時に
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.46,0:49:31.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな顔をするでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.92,0:49:37.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご一緒に格言 25:23を\N読んでみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.30,0:49:46.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,「北風は大雨をもたらし\Nうわさをする舌は怒りを招く」
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.43,0:49:49.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,パレスチナの北風は
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.60,0:49:52.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,暗い雲と雨をもたらします
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.44,0:49:57.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが話したうわさが風に乗って\N相手に届いたとします
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.19,0:49:59.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,相手はあなたに会う時
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.49,0:50:02.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,暗くて怒った顔をすることでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.49,0:50:07.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,いわば嵐が生じ\N2人の関係は悪化します
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.29,0:50:09.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたはどうしますか
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.62,0:50:13.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても後悔し 謝るかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.46,0:50:16.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 傷つけてしまった相手の評判は
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.96,0:50:19.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,元通りにはならないことがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.88,0:50:23.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダヤ人のこういう昔話があります
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.09,0:50:29.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある男が町の賢人の悪口を\N言い触らしました
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.60,0:50:33.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもその後 うわさ話を\N広めたことを後悔し
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.52,0:50:36.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,賢人に許しを求めに行きました
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.11,0:50:39.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして 償うために\N何でもすると申し出ます
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.94,0:50:42.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,賢人はあることを頼みます
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.03,0:50:47.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,「枕を切り裂いて中に詰まった\N羽根を取り出し
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.91,0:50:51.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,外にまき散らすように」\Nと言ったのです
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.37,0:50:54.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,男はそう言われて当惑しましたが
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.25,0:50:56.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,言われた通りにし
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.67,0:50:59.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,賢人にこう尋ねます
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.09,0:51:01.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,「これで許していただけますか」
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.67,0:51:06.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,賢人は「まず羽根を全部\N集めてきてください」と言います
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.68,0:51:11.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,「それは無理です 風に\Nまき散らされてしまいましたから」
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.31,0:51:13.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,賢人は言います
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.39,0:51:17.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,「あなたの言葉によって\N傷ついた私の評判も
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.86,0:51:21.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,羽根と同じように\N取り戻すことはできません」
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.74,0:51:26.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,一度口から出てしまった悪い言葉を\N取り戻すことはできないのです
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.87,0:51:30.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪い言葉という羽根を\Nまき散らさないようにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.04,0:51:33.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いうわさを広めるなら
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.29,0:51:37.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の仲間の平和が\N壊れてしまうかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.71,0:51:44.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際に起きたことを\N使徒 21:20, 21から見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.09,0:51:48.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレム会衆の長老たちは\Nパウロに 一部のユダヤ人が
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.80,0:51:53.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロについてのうわさを広めている\Nということを伝えました
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.27,0:51:55.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロが背教を説き
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.27,0:51:59.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,モーセの律法に従わないよう\N告げている と言うのです
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.19,0:52:02.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん これは事実では\Nありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.86,0:52:06.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロは律法に逆らうようなことなど\N言いませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.45,0:52:11.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,むしろ 会堂でヘブライ語聖書を使って\N教えることさえしていました
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.91,0:52:14.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,改宗してクリスチャンになった\Nユダヤ人は
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.54,0:52:16.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういううわさを聞いて
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.58,0:52:20.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,パウロが神の取り決めを無視している\Nと考えたかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.63,0:52:25.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしそういう人がいたなら\N会衆の平和は乱されたことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.72,0:52:27.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のビデオをご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.97,0:52:31.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いうわさ話は 会衆の平和を
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.81,0:52:34.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,どのように乱すことがあるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.27,0:52:38.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,あれどうなのかな？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.40,0:52:41.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓者だったら\N模範にならないといけないのに
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.02,0:52:44.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,エミリーはフォローするの\Nやめたんですか
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.57,0:52:46.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,いや でもやめるんじゃないかな
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.95,0:52:49.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,アリステア兄弟 どう思います？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.32,0:52:50.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,何のことですか
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.70,0:52:53.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリーが上げている投稿のことですよ
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.54,0:52:56.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,何か問題があったんですか
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.25,0:52:58.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,エミリーが言うには 全部
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.62,0:53:04.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私を見て！私の服\N髪 メイク」って感じで
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.21,0:53:07.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,セリア姉妹もそう思ってるって
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.30,0:53:13.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,なるほど でもSNSでは\Nその人の一部しか見えませんよね
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.85,0:53:16.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,私も失敗したことがあります
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.73,0:53:20.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,後で 間違いだったと気付いたんです
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.94,0:53:23.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういうこと ありますよね
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.27,0:53:27.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,あの ちょっと悪いんだけど
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.82,0:53:30.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,この箱 運ぶの手伝ってもらえるかな
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.95,0:53:32.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいですよ
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.71,0:53:43.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,助かったよ
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.34,0:53:44.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,いえいえ
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.84,0:53:49.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジェイク さっきの話なんだけど\N心配しているのは分かるよ
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.72,0:53:52.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも覚えておいてほしいことがあるんだ
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.76,0:53:55.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の好きな聖句なんだけどね
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.31,0:54:00.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,格言 18:17
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.64,0:54:02.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んでみて
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.19,0:54:07.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,「最初に言い分を述べる人は\N正しく見える
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.82,0:54:11.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,やがて相手方が来て 彼に問いただす」
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.78,0:54:17.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,どういうことですか
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.50,0:54:24.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,片方の言い分しか聞かないことがある\Nということを言っている聖句なんだよ
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.88,0:54:27.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,両方の言い分を聞かないうちに
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.67,0:54:30.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,判断してしまうのは良くないかもね
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.97,0:54:33.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし本当だとしても
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.51,0:54:37.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネガティブなうわさは広めたくないよね
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.60,0:54:41.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分もそういうこと されたら嫌だよね
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.77,0:54:48.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうやって考えたこと なかったです
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.78,0:54:52.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,さっきの2人に謝らないと
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.45,0:54:58.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,エミリーにも ヘイリーと話すよう\N言ってみます
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.08,0:55:01.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,それがいいね
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.71,0:55:11.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジェイクは長老から\N格言 18:17に基づく
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.22,0:55:14.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,親切なアドバイスを受けた後\N何と言いましたか
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.84,0:55:18.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,「そうやって考えたこと\Nなかったです」と言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.64,0:55:23.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジェイクはヘイリーについて\Nネガティブなことを言う前に
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.39,0:55:26.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,少し考えてみるべきでした
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.98,0:55:32.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 悪いうわさ話を「脱ぎ捨てる」\Nには どうしたらいいでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.28,0:55:37.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,格言 15:28を読んでみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.74,0:55:43.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,「正しい人は答える前に\N心の中で思い巡らし
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.79,0:55:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪人たちは悪いことを口走る」
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.50,0:55:53.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰かについて悪いことを\N言いそうになったら
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.13,0:55:55.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.26,0:55:58.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,長い時間をかける必要はありません
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.89,0:56:01.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちょっと考えるだけでいいのです
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.97,0:56:04.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジェイクは 妻から\Nヘイリーの投稿について
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.98,0:56:07.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネガティブなことを聞かされていました
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.10,0:56:10.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 聞いたことをみんなに言う前に
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.23,0:56:12.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,こう考えるべきでした
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.23,0:56:15.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,「自分が言おうとしているのは\N本当のことだろうか
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.65,0:56:19.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,これを言うのは親切なことだろうか
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.16,0:56:21.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,こういうネガティブなことを聞いたら
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.95,0:56:25.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の人たちはヘイリーのことを\Nどう思うだろう」
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.00,0:56:30.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いうわさ話を脱ぎ捨てる上で\N役立つもう1つの原則が
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.84,0:56:33.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,ルカ 6:31にあります
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.88,0:56:37.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,いわゆる黄金律です\Nイエスはこう言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.80,0:56:40.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,「人からしてほしいと思う通りに
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.93,0:56:43.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,人にもしなさい」
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.60,0:56:46.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまり 思いやりを示し
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.14,0:56:50.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,相手の身になって考えるということです\Nこう考えます
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.65,0:56:53.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,「自分がこういうことを言われたら
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.11,0:56:55.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,どう感じるだろう」
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.49,0:57:01.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いうわさ話をしたくなるかも\Nしれない1つの状況は
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.16,0:57:05.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分が誰かに傷つけられたと\N感じるときです
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.25,0:57:10.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,マタイ 5:23, 24や18:15では
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.63,0:57:15.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず相手と2人だけで話し合うよう\N勧められていますが
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.21,0:57:19.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうせずに関係のない人たちに\N話してしまうかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.89,0:57:23.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもその後 相手と話し合ったところ
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.26,0:57:28.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分が全く誤解していた\Nということに気付きます
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.19,0:57:31.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,今となってはもう手遅れです
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.73,0:57:34.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえ自分が正しくても
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.15,0:57:36.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いうわさ話をしてしまうなら
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.74,0:57:40.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,状況は悪化するだけです
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.49,0:57:46.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,うわさには話す人と聞く人がいます
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.37,0:57:49.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 聞くだけなら\N問題ないのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.83,0:57:55.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなことはありません\N格言 17:4にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.50,0:58:00.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,「悪人は有害な話に注意を向け
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.34,0:58:05.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,うそつきは悪意ある言葉に耳を傾ける」
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.56,0:58:10.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 有害で悪意ある\N話をする人だけでなく 
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.81,0:58:15.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,それに耳を傾ける人も\N罪を犯していることになります
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.07,0:58:21.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,うわさ話は聞く人がいる限り\N広まっていきます
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.20,0:58:23.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではどうしたらよいでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.41,0:58:29.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,「うわさ話は良くない」ときつく言う\N代わりに こう言えるかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.16,0:58:31.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,「話題を変えましょう」
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.21,0:58:36.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるいは「その話\N私はあまり聞きたくないな
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.17,0:58:40.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,本人がいない所で話すのはやめよう」
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.63,0:58:43.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,また ある兄弟か姉妹が
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.26,0:58:46.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,うわさ好きであることが分かったなら
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.64,0:58:50.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人と親しく\N付き合わないことによって
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.18,0:58:54.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いうわさ話を聞かずに済むでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.65,0:58:58.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,格言 20:19にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.73,0:59:03.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,「うわさ好きの人と\N交友を持ってはならない」
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.07,0:59:08.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,では兄弟姉妹 悪いうわさ話を\N脱ぎ捨てましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.95,0:59:14.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば 大切な平和と一致を\N守ることができます
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.38,0:59:18.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,統治体のケニス･クック兄弟が
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.34,0:59:20.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,このシンポジウムの最後の話をします
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.01,0:59:27.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,主題は 「平和を壊すものを\N『脱ぎ捨てる』 怒り」です
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.79,0:59:37.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,サタンは平和を破壊します
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.63,0:59:41.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書によれば サタンは\N「大きな怒り」を抱いています
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.80,0:59:45.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪意があります\N怒りを爆発させます
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.89,0:59:48.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,神を畏れる私たちが サタンのように
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.60,0:59:52.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りを爆発させることなど\Nあってよいでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.06,0:59:54.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,決してあってはなりません
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.31,0:59:58.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで私たちは そのような怒りを\N「脱ぎ捨てる」よう
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.07,1:00:00.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,努力しなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.03,1:00:05.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 怒ることはどんな場合でも\N間違っているのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.53,1:00:07.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書にはそうは書かれていません
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.91,1:00:10.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,間違っているのは\N正当な理由もないのに
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.83,1:00:14.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒ることや 怒りを爆発させることです
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.54,1:00:17.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,エフェソス 4:26にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.88,1:00:21.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,「腹が立っても\N罪を犯してはなりません」
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.59,1:00:24.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは間違っている と\N思うことを目にすると
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.51,1:00:27.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,心を乱されたりいら立ったりする\Nかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.93,1:00:31.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんな時 怒りを感じることも\Nあるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.52,1:00:34.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,それ自体は悪いことではありません
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.65,1:00:36.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,避けなければならないのは
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.69,1:00:39.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りの気持ちでいっぱいになり
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.53,1:00:42.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りを制御できなくなることです
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.36,1:00:48.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうなってしまうと 冷静に判断したり\N行動したりできなくなります
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.70,1:00:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつも怒りをぶちまける人は
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.00,1:00:53.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,永遠の命を受けられません
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.50,1:00:56.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ガラテア 5:19-21によると
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.88,1:00:59.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,「罪深い欲望から出る行い」をする人は
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.84,1:01:02.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,神の王国を授けられることはありません
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.63,1:01:07.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,「激怒」する人もそうです\N新しい世界で生きられません
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.14,1:01:10.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜでしょうか\N怒りを制御しないと
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.18,1:01:15.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分も他の人も平和では\Nなくなってしまうからです
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.06,1:01:17.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りを爆発させると
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.40,1:01:21.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人自身も周りの人たちも傷つきます
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.40,1:01:24.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,格言 29:22によると
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.03,1:01:28.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りっぽい人は「争いを引き起こし」
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.49,1:01:31.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,「多くの違反を犯」します
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.24,1:01:35.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうした違反の1つは\N暴言を吐くことです
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.29,1:01:40.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちはさまざまな機会にどう話すかを\N意識しなければなりません
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.13,1:01:44.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,同僚や伝道で会う人 会衆の兄弟姉妹
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.01,1:01:47.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族と話すときなどです
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.39,1:01:50.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪い感情が芽生えたら制御しましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.81,1:01:53.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,暴言を吐いたり あざけったり
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.60,1:01:56.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,侮辱したりするのは間違っています
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.77,1:01:58.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪感情をあらわにするなら
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.94,1:02:04.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,他の人やエホバとの大切な友情が\N壊れてしまうかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.03,1:02:09.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,噴火し続ける火山のように\Nなりたいとは思いません
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.20,1:02:13.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,噴火する火山は 周囲の人たちに\N被害を与えます
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.79,1:02:17.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,同じように 激しい怒りを\N爆発させる人は
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.42,1:02:20.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,周りの人たちを傷つけます
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.21,1:02:22.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分も傷つきます
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.34,1:02:24.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜそう言えるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.59,1:02:26.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りに任せて行動するなら
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.89,1:02:29.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りはさらにエスカレートします
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.51,1:02:33.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうなると穏やかな気持ちでは\Nいられなくなります
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.85,1:02:37.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,後悔するようなことを\Nしてしまうかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.40,1:02:40.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,健康にも悪い影響が及びます
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.61,1:02:44.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,医学研究によれば 怒りを\N制御しないと血圧が上がり
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.90,1:02:47.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,呼吸器の問題が生じることがあります
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.91,1:02:50.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,肝臓や膵臓にも影響を与え
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.87,1:02:54.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,消化器系の問題が生じることもあります
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.37,1:02:56.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,頭に血が上ると
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.50,1:02:59.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,冷静に考えることができなくなります
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.25,1:03:04.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,激しく怒った後 気分が\N落ち込んでしまう人もいます
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.34,1:03:07.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,格言 14:30にある通りです
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.89,1:03:12.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこには 「穏やかな心は\N体に良」い とあります
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.89,1:03:16.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りを爆発させると\Nどんな結果になるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.73,1:03:18.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の例を見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.90,1:03:25.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,族長ヤコブの息子\Nシメオンとレビの行ったことです
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.20,1:03:30.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人は妹のディナがシェケムに\N犯されたことを知った時 
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.08,1:03:33.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,創世記 34:7にある通り
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.45,1:03:36.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,「不快に思い 憤慨し」ました
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.96,1:03:39.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りを抱く正当な理由がありましたが
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.79,1:03:42.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,行き過ぎた行動をしてしまいました
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.17,1:03:44.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りを爆発させたのです
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.38,1:03:47.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,シメオンとレビは\Nシェケムに復讐しました
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.93,1:03:50.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,シェケムの町の人たちをだまして
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.43,1:03:53.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこに住む男たちを皆殺しにしました
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.98,1:03:58.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後ヤコブの他の息子たちは\N町の物を奪い
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.40,1:04:02.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,女性や小さな子供たちを捕らえました
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.15,1:04:04.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことを知ったヤコブはとても悲しみ
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.03,1:04:07.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,心痛を味わいました
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.57,1:04:11.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,息子たちが怒りに任せて\N行動したことを責めました
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.74,1:04:16.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,シメオンとレビは自分たちのしたことを\N正当化しようとしました
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.21,1:04:20.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバも2人の行動を\N不快に思いました
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.79,1:04:24.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブは後に神からの導きを受け
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.46,1:04:26.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,シメオンとレビの子孫が
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.80,1:04:31.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,イスラエルの中で散らされる\Nと予告しました
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.26,1:04:34.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人が怒りに任せて行動したことを
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.35,1:04:38.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,神もヤコブもとても不快に思いました
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.52,1:04:40.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書のこうした例をよく学び
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.94,1:04:43.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りを脱ぎ捨てるのは大切なことです
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.86,1:04:47.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば 悪い結果を\N身に招くことはないでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.99,1:04:50.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,次のビデオをご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.24,1:04:53.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りを制御しないとどうなってしまうか
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.16,1:04:55.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,学ぶことができます
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.71,1:05:04.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,おばあちゃん
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.59,1:05:06.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,卵忘れないでね
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.17,1:05:07.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ覚えてる 覚えてる
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.51,1:05:08.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,大丈夫？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.34,1:05:09.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,うん 大丈夫
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.26,1:05:09.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがとう
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.97,1:05:12.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,うん じゃあまたね
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.86,1:05:22.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ！
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.53,1:05:30.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリー やっと話せた\Nちょっといい？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.20,1:05:35.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,ああ エミリー 後でもいい？\N今朝はいろいろあって
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.08,1:05:39.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリーいつも忙しそうにしてるから\Nいつ話せるかなと思ってたんだけど
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.38,1:05:42.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしても話したいことがあって
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.38,1:05:45.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,分かった 何？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.84,1:05:49.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,この間上げてた投稿のことなんだけど
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.80,1:05:52.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,それが何？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.14,1:05:56.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,開拓者なのにあんなの上げて\N大丈夫なのかな と思って
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.27,1:05:58.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,何？何が言いたいの？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.81,1:06:01.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,自慢してると思われてるみたいよ
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.36,1:06:05.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,何それ？誰が？\N仕事で商品見せてるだけなのに
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.57,1:06:07.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう そうなんだけど
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.36,1:06:10.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分に注意引こうとしてるんじゃ\Nないかって思ってる人もいるよ
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.74,1:06:12.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰が言ってるの？エミリーでしょう？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.78,1:06:16.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,違う 私だけじゃないよ\Nセリア姉妹もだよ
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.16,1:06:19.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,セリア姉妹にも話したんだ！
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.67,1:06:22.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなに怒らないで ジェイクが・・・
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.29,1:06:26.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジェイクも！みんなが私のこと\N良くないって言ってるの？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.30,1:06:30.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,違うよ みんなじゃないよ ヘイリー\Nそういうことじゃなくって
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.39,1:06:33.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういうとこ あるよね\Nほんと信じらんない
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.89,1:06:37.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかに誰に話したの？\Nほんとうわさ好きだよね
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.35,1:06:38.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,うわさなんかしてない
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.60,1:06:39.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,してるじゃない！
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.69,1:06:42.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はただヘイリーのためを思って\N言っているだけ
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.36,1:06:43.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,言いたいだけでしょ！
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.02,1:06:44.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,話を聞いてってば
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.19,1:06:46.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,ちゃんと聞いてますけど
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.07,1:06:50.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんな人だと思わなかった
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.66,1:06:52.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリー 何があったの？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.74,1:06:56.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,うわさしてたでしょ！私の投稿のことで
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.58,1:07:00.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,さみしいからって\Nほかにすることないんですか？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.71,1:07:05.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヘイリー
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.59,1:07:11.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ねえ ちょっと待って！
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.89,1:07:21.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,見ていてはらはらしましたね
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.98,1:07:27.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっと この後どうなって\Nしまうんだろうと思ったことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.49,1:07:31.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここまでで 怒りを制御しないなら
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.07,1:07:33.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな結果になるかを考えました
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.78,1:07:35.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,次に考えたいのは
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.87,1:07:39.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうすれば怒りを\N脱ぎ捨てられるかということです
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.96,1:07:44.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,まず 怒りにはどんな危険が潜んで\Nいるかを理解する必要があります
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.67,1:07:48.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,格言 25:28にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.42,1:07:50.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,「怒りを抑えられない人は
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.93,1:07:55.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,城壁のない打ち破られた町のようだ」
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.26,1:07:58.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,昔 城壁は大切な役割を果たしました
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.81,1:08:03.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,城壁がなければ 敵がすぐに\N侵入してきたでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.11,1:08:06.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りを抑えられない人も同じです
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.44,1:08:10.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,かっとなると心が無防備になり
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.07,1:08:13.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,間違った考えが入ってきてしまいます
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.33,1:08:17.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうした考えは自分や\N他の人を傷つけかねません
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.70,1:08:21.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りを抑えないと\Nそういうことになるのです
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.58,1:08:23.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,危険を理解することに加えて
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.92,1:08:26.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなことが必要でしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.46,1:08:32.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りを感じたら 何かを言ったり\Nしたりする前に少し考えましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.39,1:08:34.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りが込み上げてきたら
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.51,1:08:38.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,シメオンとレビのことを\N思い出してください
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.10,1:08:41.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,先ほど見たビデオで\Nどんなことが起きていたかを
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.19,1:08:43.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,思い出すこともできます
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.90,1:08:49.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,どちらの場合も 怒りに任せて\N行動する前によく考えていれば
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.32,1:08:52.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,大変な結果にはならなかったはずです
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.82,1:08:57.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,格言 17:14もこう勧めています
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.41,1:09:00.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,「言い争いになってしまう前に
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.25,1:09:02.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこを去れ」
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.46,1:09:05.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 次の点を自問しましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.38,1:09:07.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,「全てを知っているわけではないのに
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.84,1:09:10.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,決め付けてしまうところがあるだろうか
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.63,1:09:12.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りが募る前に
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.68,1:09:17.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,そこを去って気持ちを静めることが\Nできるだろうか」
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.52,1:09:20.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブ 1:19のアドバイスは
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.35,1:09:23.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りを抑える助けになります
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.11,1:09:29.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちみんなが一生懸命に努力して\N当てはめたいアドバイスです
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.70,1:09:31.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んでみましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.78,1:09:35.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヤコブ 1:19です
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.08,1:09:41.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここには怒りを脱ぎ捨てる上で役立つ\N幾つかのことが書かれています
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.29,1:09:43.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,「覚えておいてください 皆が
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.79,1:09:47.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,人の言うことに進んで\N耳を傾けるべきです
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.09,1:09:51.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに話したり すぐに怒ったり\Nしてはなりません」
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.14,1:09:54.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,人の言うことに「進んで耳を傾け⋯⋯
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.85,1:09:57.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,すぐに話したり\Nすぐに怒ったりし」ないよう
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.89,1:10:01.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに祈って助けを求めましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.19,1:10:05.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私たちが状況をよく理解し
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.40,1:10:09.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,思いやりを示し 怒りを\N脱ぎ捨てることができるよう
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.28,1:10:11.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,助けてくださるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.36,1:10:13.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう1つ大切なのは
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.82,1:10:16.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い友達を選ぶことです
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.58,1:10:20.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,このことが大切なのはなぜでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.29,1:10:24.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまで どんなに頑張って\Nエホバに助けてもらいながら
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.25,1:10:26.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,怒りを制御してきたとしても
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.96,1:10:31.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,高慢で 頑固で\Nすぐに怒る人と付き合うなら
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.43,1:10:34.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,努力が水の泡になってしまうからです
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.01,1:10:38.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,格言 22:25には
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.18,1:10:40.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,激怒しやすい人の「行いを
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.56,1:10:44.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,まねるようになっては\Nならない」とあります
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.27,1:10:48.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちはこの大会のプログラムを通して
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.44,1:10:52.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,警戒を怠らず 立派な行動を続け
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.57,1:10:56.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,新しい世界で生きるのに\N必要なことを学んでいます
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.95,1:10:59.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてこのシンポジウムでは
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.54,1:11:04.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を壊すものを脱ぎ捨てる努力を\N続けるよう励まされました
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.29,1:11:08.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,その中には 自慢 ねたみ 不正直
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.76,1:11:12.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪いうわさ話 怒りなどがあります
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.63,1:11:16.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分が何かの点で改善しなければ\Nならないことに気付くなら
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.72,1:11:18.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに助けを求め
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.89,1:11:21.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,一生懸命に努力し
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.19,1:11:23.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,変化するようにしましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.77,1:11:29.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 兄弟姉妹と平和な関係を\N築くよう真剣に努力しましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.36,1:11:36.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバの日」と新しい世界を心から\N待ち望んでいる人はそうするはずです
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.28,1:11:38.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,天のお父さんエホバは
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.66,1:11:42.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの誠実な努力に\N目を留めてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.92,1:11:45.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,これからも エホバとの
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.96,1:11:49.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして仲間との平和な関係を\N築いていきましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.01,1:11:52.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば 憐れみ深いエホバは
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.80,1:11:58.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちを「汚点も傷もない平和な人」\Nと見てくださるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.06,1:12:05.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,一致の絆を強めるのに役立つ話を\Nありがとうございました
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.48,1:12:08.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,エデンでの反逆以来
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.90,1:12:13.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,人類の間には\Nほとんど平和が見られていません
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.20,1:12:16.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもエホバは ご自分に頼る人たちに
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.95,1:12:19.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を与えてこられました
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.12,1:12:23.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,過去にどのように\Nそうしてこられましたか
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.17,1:12:27.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことは今どのように\N信仰を強めるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.38,1:12:31.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではこれから\N「エホバは平和へと導いてくださる」
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.47,1:12:33.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,第1部が始まります
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.68,1:12:36.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうぞご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.17,1:13:12.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間はこれまでずっと\N平和を願ってきました
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.30,1:13:21.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,一人一人の平和
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.77,1:13:26.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族の平和
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.57,1:13:32.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,全人類の平和です
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.36,1:14:18.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間は平和のために\Nいろいろな事をしてきましたが 
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.45,1:14:22.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,どれもうまくいっていません
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.97,1:14:45.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,何世紀にもわたって指導者たちは
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.73,1:14:48.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和のために 条約を結んだり
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.65,1:14:52.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,決議を採択したり 会談を開いたりし 
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.32,1:14:55.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,皮肉にも戦争さえしてきました
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.41,1:15:05.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,人類の平和は今
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.62,1:15:08.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,かつてないほど脅かされています
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.04,1:15:12.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和を実現するための人間の試みは
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.34,1:15:15.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,何度も何度も失敗してきました
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.71,1:15:18.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは驚くようなことではありません
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.76,1:15:22.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,エレミヤ10章23節にあるように
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.35,1:15:26.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,「人は⋯⋯自分で自分の歩みを\N導くことが」できません
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.68,1:15:31.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,元々 人間が人間を治めることには\N無理があるのです
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.86,1:15:35.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,健康 安全 安心感
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.44,1:15:39.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,これらは聖書が言う\N「終わりの時代」が進むにつれて 
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.36,1:15:42.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,ますます失われていっています
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.62,1:15:45.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,人間が人間を治める限り
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.08,1:15:48.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,争いや対立は無くなりません
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.16,1:15:53.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなに努力しても 人間の力では\N世界を平和にはできません
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.34,1:15:58.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 神との絆があれば\N安心して暮らすことができます
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.13,1:16:01.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,イザヤ48章にはこうあります
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.05,1:16:03.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私エホバは あなたの神である
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.85,1:16:06.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたのためになる生き方を教え
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.52,1:16:09.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたを導いて正しい道を歩ませる
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.02,1:16:13.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが私のおきてに\N注意を払いさえすれば！
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.48,1:16:18.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば あなたの平和は\N川の流れのように豊かにな［る］」
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.49,1:16:20.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,人類を導いて
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.53,1:16:22.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界を平和な場所にできるのは
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.03,1:16:25.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバだけです
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.24,1:16:27.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうエホバは約束しています
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.83,1:16:30.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,その時が来るまで安心して暮らせるよう
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.96,1:16:35.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私たちを助けてくれます\Nどのようにしてでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.46,1:16:37.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,「人間の理解をはるかに超え」た
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.59,1:16:41.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,「神からの平和」を\N与えることによってです
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.15,1:16:58.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和が失われそうに\Nなったことがあるのは
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.23,1:17:01.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,現代の私たちだけではありません
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.15,1:17:05.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書には同じような経験をした人が\Nたくさん出てきます
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.99,1:17:08.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人たちがどのようにエホバに頼り
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.91,1:17:11.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,助けてもらったかを考えると
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.08,1:17:16.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちを平和へと導いてくださる\Nエホバへの信頼が強まります
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.29,1:17:18.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういう記録は 
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.30,1:17:22.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが神の王国によって実現させる\N平和と関連があります
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.93,1:17:25.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが私たちを必ず助け
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.55,1:17:29.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和へと導いてくださるという\N確信を持たせてくれます
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.81,1:17:33.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうやってエホバに\N助けてもらった人の1人に
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.14,1:17:35.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨナがいます
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.81,1:17:39.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨナは紀元前9世紀の預言者です
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.78,1:17:45.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨナはエホバから アッシリア帝国の\N都市ニネベに行くようにと言われます
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.57,1:17:48.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニネベがどんな都市かを知っていたので
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.08,1:17:51.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨナは恐れと不安で\Nいっぱいになりました
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.50,1:17:55.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,アッシリアの兵士たちは\N残虐なことで知られ
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.71,1:18:00.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニネベは後に「流血に満ちた都市」\Nと呼ばれるようになりました
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.71,1:18:03.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 異教の神を信じる人たちに
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.67,1:18:06.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,都市の滅亡を知らせるように\Nと言われた時
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.93,1:18:10.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨナが恐怖に襲われたのもうなずけます
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.85,1:18:16.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,何とか身を守るために
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.90,1:18:20.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨナはニネベから\N遠く離れた所に行こうとし
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.52,1:18:23.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,タルシシュ行きの船に乗ります
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.16,1:18:31.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,タルシシュは 現在のスペインに\Nあったと考えられています
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.45,1:18:33.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでイスラエルから見ると
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.70,1:18:37.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニネベとは全く逆の方向に\N行ったことが分かります
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.17,1:18:40.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 身を守るどころか
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.54,1:18:43.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,かえって危険にさらされます
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.93,1:18:49.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,うわあ！
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.01,1:18:52.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,船長！
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.73,1:18:57.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,まずいな 
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.77,1:19:00.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,帆をたため！
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.20,1:19:08.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは普通の嵐ではありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.86,1:19:10.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,猛烈な雨風にさらされ
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.95,1:19:13.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,船は沈みそうになりました
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.33,1:19:15.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,船長！水が大量に入ってきます
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.91,1:19:18.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは神々のたたりだ！
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.50,1:19:20.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,バアルよ！
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.08,1:19:21.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,エシュムン様！
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.79,1:19:26.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,船員たちは自分の神に呼び掛けますが\Nヨナは分かっていました
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.42,1:19:28.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,これはエホバだと
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.05,1:19:33.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで責任を感じ\N自分のせいだと打ち明けます
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.27,1:19:37.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,私を持ち上げて海に投げ込めば 
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.23,1:19:39.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,静まるでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.31,1:19:44.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,この大嵐が生じているのは\N私のせいだと分かっているからです
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.32,1:19:48.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうやって自分から名乗り出るためには
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.24,1:19:51.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,相当の勇気が必要だったはずです
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.57,1:19:54.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが助けてくれるかどうかは\N分かりませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.79,1:19:59.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 自分のせいで人が死ぬのは\N耐えられませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.09,1:20:14.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはヨナを思いやり\N助けの手を差し伸べます
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.31,1:20:16.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしてまだ生きてるんだ？
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.06,1:20:19.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はどうなるんだろう？
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.94,1:20:22.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,難しい任務を前にして
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.44,1:20:27.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨナはエホバから逃げて\Nタルシシュに行こうとしました
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.65,1:20:29.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨナの良心は痛み始めます
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.90,1:20:33.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんなことをして本当に\N良かったのだろうか
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.20,1:20:36.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分で何とかしようとしてしまいました
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.16,1:20:38.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分で自分の身を守ろうとしました
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.66,1:20:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,その結果 今どこにいるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.04,1:20:43.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,魚の腹の中です
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.25,1:20:47.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨナは悔いる気持ちで\Nエホバに助けを求めます
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.30,1:20:50.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバよ
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.18,1:20:54.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,シェオルの腹の中から
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.85,1:20:57.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,助けを叫び求めます
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.06,1:21:01.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の声を聞いてください
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.94,1:21:04.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の誓約したことを
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.02,1:21:07.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は果たします
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.11,1:21:10.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨナはもうエホバの預言者として
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.70,1:21:14.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,務めを果たすことはないと\N思ったかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.58,1:21:20.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,何しろ 指示に従いませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.41,1:21:24.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでエホバから\Nもう一度指示があった時
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.92,1:21:27.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても驚いたことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.22,1:21:37.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨナ！
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.81,1:21:42.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,立って 大いなる都市ニネベに行き
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.44,1:21:47.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,私があなたに語る布告をふれ告げよ
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.07,1:21:50.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,はい 分かりました
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.90,1:21:53.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,ありがとうございます
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.24,1:22:01.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初ヨナは自分で何とかしようとし
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.00,1:22:06.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが残虐なアッシリア人から\N守ってくれるとは考えませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.83,1:22:09.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 2回目はどうだったでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.80,1:22:12.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,あれこれと心配するのはやめて
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.30,1:22:16.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが守ってくれると\N信じて行動しました
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.77,1:22:30.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,あとわずか40日で ニネベは倒される
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.65,1:22:33.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,まことの神エホバは言われた
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.86,1:22:35.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,この都市は滅ぼされる
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.95,1:22:38.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニネベは倒される
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.41,1:22:41.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,まことの神はニネベを倒される
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.87,1:22:45.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,まことの神は言われた
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.96,1:22:48.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,やがて 王自ら心を入れ替え
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.42,1:22:52.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニネベの人たちにも同じように\Nするようにと命令を出します
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.80,1:22:57.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,この出来事からヨナは\N大切なことを学びました
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.68,1:22:59.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初はニネベから逃げて
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.72,1:23:02.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを信頼するのではなく
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.10,1:23:05.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分で何とかしようとしました
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.81,1:23:08.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたがヨナですか
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.15,1:23:09.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうだよ
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.27,1:23:12.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,ママはあなたのおかげだって言ってた
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.15,1:23:16.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,いや エホバのおかげだよ
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.82,1:23:18.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はただ
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.78,1:23:22.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,言われたことを伝えただけだ
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.12,1:23:25.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨナは学びました
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.16,1:23:29.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを信頼して言われる通りに\Nすれば 必ず守ってもらえます
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.75,1:23:31.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの場合も同じです
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.92,1:23:34.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバから 「これをやってみなさい
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.13,1:23:36.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,こちらに進みなさい」と言われる時
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.80,1:23:40.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは必ず道を切り開いてくれます
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.26,1:23:43.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのことを確信できます
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.10,1:23:47.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,ニネベの人たちは心を入れ替えたので
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.23,1:23:49.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,この時は救われましたが
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.73,1:23:54.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,アッシリアはやがて\N再び悪い道に進むようになります
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.44,1:23:58.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨナの時から約1世紀が過ぎ
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.45,1:24:00.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,アッシリアの王セナケリブは
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.66,1:24:03.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダの町々に次々と攻め入ります
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.91,1:24:07.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,目指すはエルサレムの陥落です
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.50,1:24:11.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダのヒゼキヤ王は
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.54,1:24:15.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバにしっかり」従う\N素晴らしい王でした
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.21,1:24:17.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,王になった最初の頃から
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.30,1:24:19.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダだけでなくイスラエル全体で
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.72,1:24:22.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,正しい崇拝を熱心に広めました
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.97,1:24:27.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヒゼキヤはエホバの崇拝のために\N力を尽くしてきましたが
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.14,1:24:29.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,今や セナケリブの軍隊により
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.94,1:24:33.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムは侵略の危機に面しています
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.53,1:24:39.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヒゼキヤは平和のために
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.61,1:24:43.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,セナケリブの要求に応じて\N金銀を支払います
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.16,1:24:46.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし セナケリブは侵略を続け
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.24,1:24:50.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,強固に防備された町\Nラキシュを包囲します
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.92,1:24:58.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,セナケリブはそこから軍隊の一部と\N長官たちをエルサレムに送り
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.92,1:25:01.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,降伏を迫ろうとします
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.84,1:25:06.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,代表して話すのは ヘブライ語を\N上手に話せるラブシャケです
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.93,1:25:11.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,ラブシャケは大声でヒゼキヤをののしり\Nエホバをあざけります
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.94,1:25:17.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバなどセナケリブ王の前では\N全くの無力だ」と言います
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.40,1:25:21.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,聞いていた兵士たちがどう思ったか\N考えてみてください
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.53,1:25:26.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,セナケリブの軍隊は ほかの町を\N次から次へと攻め取っています
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.70,1:25:31.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヒゼキヤはどうするか\N決めなければいけません
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.16,1:25:33.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の力で何とかするでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.54,1:25:37.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,それとも エホバの力を\N信頼するでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.55,1:25:44.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは過去と同様
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.22,1:25:46.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちを助けることも\N十分にできるのです
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.81,1:25:48.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヒゼキヤ王！
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.73,1:25:54.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,まだ現実が見えないのですか
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.27,1:25:57.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,わなに掛かった鳥のようです
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.19,1:26:02.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは何も悪いことは起きない\Nという考えにしがみついている
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.40,1:26:04.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは神殿やエルサレム
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.74,1:26:07.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして私たちを\N滅ぼそうとしているのです
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.83,1:26:11.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,私は危険を理解していますし\N恐れてもいます
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.87,1:26:16.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしエホバがエルサレムの滅びを\N許されるなら それでもよいのです
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.79,1:26:21.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 私たちがエホバのものを\Nどうして引き渡せるでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.17,1:26:26.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヒゼキヤはエホバの力を\N信じることにしました
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.09,1:26:29.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえセナケリブの軍隊が\Nエルサレムに向かってきているとしても
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.85,1:26:33.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバなら救うことができる\Nと考えました
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.73,1:26:39.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はおまえたちの王に興味があるんだ
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.98,1:26:44.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼は誰が私から救い出してくれる\Nと思っているのかね
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.53,1:26:51.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,おまえたちの神 エホバは弱いんだ！
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.37,1:26:58.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバも私の神 アシュルの前で\N縮み上がっているんだろう
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.75,1:27:03.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヒゼキヤはエホバを信頼\Nし続けることにしました
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.55,1:27:07.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうするには相当の信仰が\N必要だったはずです
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.76,1:27:12.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,何しろ18万5000人以上もの\Nアッシリア軍が
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.31,1:27:15.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムに向かってきているのです
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.73,1:27:22.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつ攻撃されても\Nおかしくない状況でしたが
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.53,1:27:26.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヒゼキヤは自分で\N何とかしようとするのではなく 
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.66,1:27:31.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,安心を求めてエホバに頼り続けました
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.54,1:27:40.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはこのたびも どんなに強い\N人間の王たちであっても
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.34,1:27:45.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの前では何の力も\Nないことを証明します
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.82,1:28:06.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヒゼキヤはもう駄目だと\N思えるようなときでも
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.15,1:28:11.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを信頼するなら必ず\N道が開けることを学びました
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.49,1:28:15.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはアッシリア軍を打ち破り\N信頼に応えてくれました
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.87,1:28:18.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは私たちもずっと\N覚えておきたいことです
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.62,1:28:20.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,今も 将来もです
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.67,1:28:23.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,この先 危険な目に遭うことが\Nあるかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.96,1:28:26.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 忘れてはいけません
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.05,1:28:28.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに不可能なことはありません
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.55,1:28:30.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは導いてくれます
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.68,1:28:33.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,信頼して しっかり付いて\Nいくことが大切です
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.93,1:28:38.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば エホバは\Nハルマゲドンの時に守ってくれます
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.69,1:28:43.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムはこのたびは\N敵の攻撃から守られましたが
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.27,1:28:47.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和な時期は長くは続きませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.82,1:28:53.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヒゼキヤの子マナセは エホバから見て\N忌まわしいことを行いました
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.83,1:28:56.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,バアル崇拝を復興させたばかりか
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.66,1:28:59.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,それをより大々的に行い
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.46,1:29:04.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,異教の彫刻像をエホバの\N神殿の中に置くことさえしました
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.80,1:29:07.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,少し考えてみてください
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.34,1:29:10.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,本来なら間違った崇拝から\N国民を守るべき王が
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.93,1:29:15.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,正反対のことをし\N異教の神の祭壇を作っています
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.14,1:29:18.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかも自分の子供たちを火で焼いて
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.14,1:29:21.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,異教の神に犠牲として\N捧げることさえしました
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.90,1:29:26.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヒゼキヤが国民のために\N築き上げた神との平和な関係が
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.44,1:29:30.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,今やその息子によって\N壊されてしまいました
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.74,1:29:33.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでエホバはマナセを\N厳しく処罰します
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.99,1:29:38.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,マナセはアッシリアの王に捕らえられ\Nバビロンに連れていかれます
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.62,1:29:42.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,マナセは牢屋の中で\N心から悔い改めました
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.67,1:29:47.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,心を入れ替え その後はずっと\Nエホバだけを崇拝するようになりました
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.67,1:29:49.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,おじいちゃん！
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.30,1:29:52.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバだけを崇拝することが\Nどれほど大切かを
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.68,1:29:55.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,孫のヨシヤにしっかり\N教えたことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.93,1:29:58.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,話したいことがある
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.10,1:30:02.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは聖なる方で
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.69,1:30:05.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,おまえはエホバが望まれる仕方で
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.52,1:30:09.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,ただエホバだけに仕えなければならない
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.90,1:30:14.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,ほかの神には何の力もない
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.70,1:30:17.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,それにもかかわらず 人々はまだ
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.79,1:30:22.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとバアルの両方に\N仕えられると考えています
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.12,1:30:24.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで ヨシヤは王になった後
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.58,1:30:28.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,偶像崇拝根絶のために動き出します
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.09,1:30:30.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,よそじゃもっと安かったぞ
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.26,1:30:34.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,買わないならいいわよ
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.93,1:30:43.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,ここからだ！
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.81,1:30:47.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,ワーッ！
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.66,1:31:01.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,この国の偶像は全てこうなる
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.00,1:31:06.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤは異教の祭壇を取り壊し
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.96,1:31:09.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖木や偶像を打ち砕きました
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.88,1:31:13.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,国から偶像崇拝を一掃するためです
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.42,1:31:15.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,偶像崇拝がはびこる中で
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.76,1:31:21.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,真の崇拝のために恐れることなく\N勇気を出して立ち上がりました
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.39,1:31:24.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,決して簡単なことではありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.89,1:31:29.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,これでよいのだろうか と\N不安になることもあったでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.27,1:31:35.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,おそらくエホバは預言者エレミヤを\N通して ヨシヤを励ましたことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.70,1:31:39.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはこう言っている
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.41,1:31:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ヨシヤという男の子が\Nダビデ家に生まれる
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.25,1:31:51.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,その人は 高い場所の祭司たちを\Nあなたの上で犠牲として捧げる
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.96,1:31:56.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの上で犠牲の煙を\N立ち上らせている祭司たちをである」
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.80,1:32:02.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,300年以上前に語られた\Nこの預言の言葉は
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.60,1:32:04.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,紛れもなくヨシヤこそが
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.02,1:32:09.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,間違った崇拝を終わらせる\N王であることをはっきり示していました
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.65,1:32:12.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでヨシヤは これでいいんだと思い
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.65,1:32:18.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,ますます自信を持って 神殿の修復\Nなどの改革を進めたはずです
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.66,1:32:22.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのおかけでエホバだけが\N崇拝されるようになり
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.12,1:32:25.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和な時代がやって来ました
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.62,1:32:30.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのために一生懸命だった\Nヨシヤに私たちは引かれます
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.54,1:32:33.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 人々の心は腐りきっていて
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.42,1:32:37.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,厳しい処罰がどうしても必要でした
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.43,1:32:42.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダはバビロニア人に征服される\Nとエレミヤは預言しました
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.72,1:32:46.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,この土地は荒廃する
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.81,1:32:52.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたたちは70年の間\Nバビロンの王に仕えなければならない
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.44,1:32:56.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,エレミヤがそう預言するのを\Nダニエルも聞いたかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.57,1:33:02.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,預言はその通りになり 自分も家族も\Nバビロンに連れていかれました
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.91,1:33:05.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,不安でいっぱいだったはずです
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.16,1:33:07.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは将来を\N期待される若者でしたが
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.00,1:33:12.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,連れてこられ 家族からも\N引き離されました
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.92,1:33:16.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかも ネブカドネザル王の宮廷で
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.80,1:33:19.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,特別な訓練を受けることになり
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.30,1:33:21.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,不安はいっそう募ります
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.01,1:33:24.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,バビロニア人の生活は
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.06,1:33:28.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルが育ったユダでの生活とは\Nまるで違っていました
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.31,1:33:30.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも ダニエルは エホバが\N禁じた食べ物で
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.98,1:33:34.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分を汚すことはしない\Nと決意していました
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.94,1:33:40.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうやって頑張るダニエルを\Nエホバは後押しし
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.36,1:33:45.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは王の下で働く\N賢人の1人に選ばれます
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.63,1:33:58.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネブカドネザルは国々を攻め取って\N大帝国を築こうとしていました
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.26,1:34:01.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,紀元前624年に王位に就いてから
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.55,1:34:05.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,侵略を続け 領土を\N広げていっていました
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.81,1:34:10.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,バビロンは貿易と商業の\N中心地になっていました
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.44,1:34:14.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,王は都市の周りに 強固な城壁を築き
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.86,1:34:18.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,今やバビロンは難攻不落に思えました
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.82,1:34:20.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,バビロンに住んでいた人たちは
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.99,1:34:26.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,こんな城壁に囲まれていれば絶対に\N安心だと思っていたことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.87,1:34:31.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネブカドネザルは都市の\N繁栄と安全は全て
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.62,1:34:34.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の神々のおかげだ\Nと考えていました
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.04,1:34:39.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのうちの一番の神は\N戦争の神マルドゥクでした
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.80,1:34:46.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも そうした神々や祭司たちは\N全く無能でした
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.64,1:34:51.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,ある夜 ネブカドネザル王は\N奇妙な夢を見ます
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.65,1:35:03.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,賢人たちを呼べ！
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.07,1:35:06.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が生き続けますように\Nどのような夢かお話しください
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.70,1:35:08.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうすれば解き明かします
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.79,1:35:10.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,なんだと！
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.62,1:35:14.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,もしおまえたちが夢の内容を話さず\N解き明かさないなら
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.79,1:35:19.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,手足を切り取って おまえたちの家を\N公衆便所にしてやる
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.17,1:35:23.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,無理です そんなこと誰にもできません
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.51,1:35:25.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,難し過ぎます
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.59,1:35:30.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,王に説明できるのは 神々だけでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.56,1:35:37.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,捕らえろ！
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.40,1:35:40.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,処刑しろ！
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.82,1:35:43.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,エラハ
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.19,1:35:44.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,逃げてください
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.32,1:35:45.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,何かあったのか？
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.41,1:35:50.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,詳しくは分かりませんが 賢人たちが\N王の逆鱗に触れて 明朝処刑されます
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.70,1:35:53.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハナニア ミシャエル アザリヤを\N連れてきてください
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.62,1:35:55.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,相談します
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.71,1:35:57.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が出したこの命令によれば
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.75,1:36:01.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルと仲間たちも\N殺されることになります
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.30,1:36:04.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,この時 ダニエルは\Nどう感じたでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.09,1:36:06.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,若くして異国の地に連れてこられ
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.30,1:36:10.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,世界で最も権力のある残忍な王の\N宮廷で仕えています
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.85,1:36:14.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,その王がとんでもない\N無理難題を吹っ掛けてきます
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.48,1:36:17.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,「誰かいないのか\N夢の内容を話せ
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.65,1:36:20.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,意味を解き明かせ」
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.11,1:36:24.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,王よ
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.53,1:36:27.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の神エホバなら解き明かせます
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.53,1:36:31.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,王が見た夢と その意味を
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.49,1:36:36.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,じゃあ おまえの神の言葉を聞かせろ！
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.42,1:36:39.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはきっと
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.83,1:36:42.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,いや必ず夢を解き明かしてくださいます
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.88,1:36:46.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうか時間をください
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.01,1:36:51.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは経験があったので\Nそう言ったのではありません
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.01,1:36:55.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,これまでエホバから夢の解き明かしを\N受けたことはありません
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.64,1:36:58.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,彼を動かしていたのは信仰でした
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.35,1:37:03.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時読めた聖なる書物を\N学ぶことによって得た信仰です
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.53,1:37:06.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうした書物の中には モーセ ダビデ
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.95,1:37:11.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,ソロモン イザヤ エレミヤなどが\N書いた書物があったはずです
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.83,1:37:16.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルはきっと そうした巻物を\N真剣に読んでいたことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.71,1:37:22.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,心からエホバに祈り 知恵と理解を\N与えてくださいとお願いしたはずです
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.09,1:37:24.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても大切な時間でした
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.38,1:37:27.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうやって神の言葉を学ぶことにより
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.55,1:37:30.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルの信仰は強まりました
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.22,1:37:33.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとの絆もますます深まりました
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.68,1:37:37.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネブカドネザル王の夢について\N何も知りませんでしたが
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.35,1:37:39.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルは確信していました
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.52,1:37:43.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,それがどんな夢で どんな意味が\Nあるかをエホバが教えてくれて
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.90,1:37:47.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,命を救ってくれることを
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.61,1:37:52.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルはこの時 聖書の\Nどの書物を調べたのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.66,1:37:54.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエル書によれば 少なくとも
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.83,1:37:58.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,幾つかの書物を参照することが\Nできたようです
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.41,1:38:01.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,エレミヤの書物への言及があります
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.29,1:38:06.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに頼った人たちがどのように\N助けてもらったかを学びました
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.30,1:38:08.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで 時間をくださいと言ったのは
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.63,1:38:12.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,命を少しでも伸ばそうと\Nしたからではありません
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.22,1:38:14.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが信頼に応えて
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.26,1:38:18.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,夢を解き明かしてくれると\N信じていたからです
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.14,1:38:22.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルはただ信じただけでは\Nありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.65,1:38:27.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが必ず夢の解き明かしを\Nしてくれると確信していましたが
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.86,1:38:32.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,何もせずに成り行きに任せるような\Nことはしませんでした
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.28,1:38:35.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに心から祈りました
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.28,1:38:39.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,神に仕える人みんなにとって\N素晴らしい手本です
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.75,1:38:44.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバ ここに来たのは\N死ぬためではないはずです
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.58,1:38:48.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,この国の人たちはどう思うでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.21,1:38:50.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたが天の神で
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.30,1:38:54.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,秘密を明らかにする本当の神だと\N言ってしまいました
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.05,1:39:00.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうか 力をお示しください
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.89,1:39:43.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,ユダで捕らえた人の中で王の夢を\N解き明かせる者を見つけました
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.19,1:39:45.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰かは分かっている
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.19,1:39:49.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,おまえは本当に私が見た夢の内容を話し
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.57,1:39:52.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,解き明かせるのか
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.12,1:40:08.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,秘密を明らかにされる神が\N天におられます
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.84,1:40:13.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,その方が 最後の日々に起きる事柄を
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.13,1:40:16.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,ネブカドネザル王に知らせたのです
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.60,1:40:21.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,これが あなたが見た夢です
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.23,1:40:31.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,王は巨大な像をご覧になりました
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.62,1:40:43.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,その像があなたの前に立っていました
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.62,1:40:49.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたこそが金の頭です
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.59,1:40:52.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたの後に 劣った別の王国
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.96,1:40:55.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,銀のものが生じます
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.76,1:40:57.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,次いで別の王国
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.89,1:41:00.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,3番目の銅のものが生じ
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.26,1:41:03.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,全世界を支配します
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.35,1:41:09.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,4番目の王国は 鉄のように\N強いものとなります
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.06,1:41:13.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,この王国は分裂することになります
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.36,1:41:17.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,足の指には鉄の部分と\N粘土の部分があるので
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.74,1:41:22.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,この王国には強い部分と\Nもろい部分があることになります
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.08,1:41:31.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルがこうするには 相当の\N信仰と勇気が必要でした
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.29,1:41:34.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも不安に襲われることや
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.09,1:41:37.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,命が危うくなることが\Nあるかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.76,1:41:43.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういう時 ダニエルのように心から\Nエホバに祈りたいと思います
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.60,1:41:47.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,助けてくれると信じて祈ります
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.27,1:41:52.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちもダニエルとヨナと同じような\N任務をエホバから受けています
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.07,1:41:57.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,神を認めようとしない人たちが\Nどうなるかをはっきり伝えるのは
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.32,1:41:59.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,とても勇気のいることです
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.86,1:42:01.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,この2人の預言者から
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.91,1:42:07.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを信頼すれば必ず助けて\Nもらえるということが分かります
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.37,1:42:09.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが信仰を捨てない限り
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.87,1:42:13.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはいつもそばにいてくれます
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.29,1:42:18.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえヒゼキヤのように絶体絶命だと\N思える状況になったとしても
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.63,1:42:23.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな力よりも強い聖なる力を\Nエホバからもらうことができます
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.76,1:42:26.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,この体制の終わりが近づくにつれ
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.60,1:42:29.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの勇気が試されたり
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.06,1:42:32.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和が脅かされたりする時が必ず来ます
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.77,1:42:35.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを揺るぎなく\N支持しなければいけません
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.77,1:42:38.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨシヤのようにです
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.15,1:42:40.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,周りはそうしないかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.24,1:42:42.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも エホバが共にいてくれるので
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.53,1:42:44.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなことがあっても大丈夫です
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.91,1:42:48.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,誰よりも強いエホバが助けてくれます
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.29,1:42:51.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,注目したいことがあります
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.37,1:42:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダニエルが書いた預言の言葉は
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.04,1:42:59.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,バビロニア帝国がどうなるかだけを\N明らかにしていたわけではありません
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.13,1:43:01.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,その後から現代に至るまで
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.47,1:43:05.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして将来世界がどうなるかも\N明らかにしていました
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.76,1:43:09.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,その予告されていたことが\N実際に起きているのを
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.10,1:43:13.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,今 私たちはこの目で見ています
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.49,1:43:23.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,考えさせられる内容でした
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.36,1:43:25.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,平和が脅かされる時も
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.83,1:43:30.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の忠誠がエホバの目的と\Nどう関係するかに注意を集中し
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.91,1:43:35.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして喜びを持って\N忍耐することができます
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.08,1:43:38.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,大会の3日目午後の部分で\N見ることができる
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.55,1:43:42.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,第2部の内容も本当に楽しみです
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.72,1:43:45.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,では ご一緒に130番の歌
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.64,1:43:48.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,「進んで許す」を歌いましょう
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.81,1:43:51.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,歌は130番です
